{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775864189951,"sessionID":"ses_2863f3b4dffeWWPksoHTtGvb3O","part":{"id":"prt_d79c104a2001Ef1aHS1PFvkEmD","messageID":"msg_d79c0edbc0011hbhimeCRbc48d","sessionID":"ses_2863f3b4dffeWWPksoHTtGvb3O","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_046098e46d6f4c6cab00629a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/AR-015-proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/AR-015-proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-015: PicoD Command Execution API\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: This proposal implements the PicoD command execution API for the `pkg/picod` module in the AgentCube project. The goal is to:\n6: \n7: 1. **Secure Command Execution** - Execute commands within controlled sandbox environments with proper isolation\n8: 2. **Resource Limit Enforcement** - Enforce CPU, memory, time, and output size limits on command execution\n9: 3. **Output Capture and Streaming** - Capture stdout/stderr with optional streaming for long-running commands\n10: 4. **Cancellation Support** - Enable command cancellation via context for graceful termination\n11: 5. **Security Hardening** - Implement security validations to prevent privilege escalation and command injection\n12: \n13: This implementation builds upon the sandbox infrastructure established in AR-012 and provides the execution engine for code interpreters and agent runtimes.\n14: \n15: ## Scope\n16: \n17: **Module:** `pkg/picod`  \n18: **Language:** Go  \n19: **Size:** M\n20: \n21: This AR covers:\n22: \n23: - **In scope:**\n24:   - Core `PicoD` struct and initialization (`picod.go`)\n25:   - Command execution logic with resource limits (`executor.go`)\n26:   - Resource limit configuration and enforcement (`limits.go`)\n27:   - Output capture and streaming (`output.go`)\n28:   - Security validations and sandboxing (`security.go`)\n29:   - Unit tests with mocked executors\n30:   - Integration tests with real command execution\n31:   - Configuration via environment variables\n32: \n33: - **Out of scope:**\n34:   - Container runtime integration (covered in AR-005, AR-009)\n35:   - Network namespace manipulation\n36:   - User namespace management\n37:   - Filesystem isolation beyond chroot/workspace jail\n38:   - Distributed command execution\n39:   - PicoD HTTP daemon (covered in `code-execution/` specs)\n40: \n41: ## Current State Analysis\n42: \n43: ### Existing Sandbox Infrastructure\n44: \n45: The current system has sandbox management infrastructure:\n46: \n47: 1. **Sandbox Manager** (`pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox/`):\n48:    - Creates and manages sandbox pods\n49:    - Handles lifecycle (create, update, delete)\n50:    - Supports warm pool for pre-provisioned sandboxes\n51: \n52: 2. **CodeInterpreter CRD** (`pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`):\n53:    - Defines `CodeInterpreterSpec` with image, command, args, env, resources\n54:    - Supports `AuthMode` enum (`picod` or `none`)\n55:    - Default image: `volcanosh/picod:latest`\n56: \n57: 3. **Workload Manager**:\n58:    - Handles `CodeInterpreter` resources\n59:    - Creates underlying sandbox pods\n60:    - Injects `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` when `AuthMode=picod`\n61: \n62: ### Gaps Identified\n63: \n64: 1. **No unified execution API** - Command execution logic is scattered or non-existent\n65: 2. **No resource limit enforcement** - No programmatic way to enforce CPU/memory/time limits\n66: 3. **No output streaming** - Cannot stream output for long-running commands\n67: 4. **No security hardening** - Missing input validation and sandboxing at the API level\n68: 5. **No cancellation support** - Cannot gracefully cancel running commands\n69: \n70: ### PicoD Context\n71: \n72: Per `code-execution/design.md` and `code-execution/spec.md`:\n73: - PicoD is an HTTP daemon that runs commands inside a configurable workspace jail\n74: - Exposes health endpoint with JWT (RSA)-protected APIs\n75: - CLI flags: `-port` (default 8080), `-workspace` (default: current working directory)\n76: - Server uses `ReadHeaderTimeout` of 10 seconds\n77: \n78: ## Proposed Changes\n79: \n80: ### 1. Core PicoD Structure (`picod.go`)\n81: \n82: ```go\n83: // PicoD represents a command execution sandbox\n84: type PicoD struct {\n85:     sandboxID    string\n86:     workDir      string\n87:     limits       *ResourceLimits\n88:     securityOpts *SecurityOptions\n89:     logger       klog.Logger\n90: }\n91: \n92: // Option is a functional option for PicoD\n93: type Option func(*PicoD)\n94: \n95: // New creates a new PicoD instance\n96: func New(sandboxID string, opts ...Option) *PicoD\n97: \n98: // WithWorkDir sets the working directory\n99: func WithWorkDir(dir string) Option\n100: \n101: // WithLimits sets resource limits\n102: func WithLimits(limits *ResourceLimits) Option\n103: \n104: // WithSecurityOpts sets security options\n105: func WithSecurityOpts(opts *SecurityOptions) Option\n106: \n107: // WithLogger sets the logger\n108: func WithLogger(logger klog.Logger) Option\n109: ```\n110: \n111: ### 2. Resource Limits (`limits.go`)\n112: \n113: ```go\n114: // ResourceLimits defines execution resource limits\n115: type ResourceLimits struct {\n116:     // Timeout is the maximum execution duration\n117:     Timeout time.Duration\n118:     \n119:     // MaxCPU is the maximum CPU cores (e.g., 0.5, 1.0)\n120:     MaxCPU float64\n121:     \n122:     // MaxMemory is the maximum memory in bytes\n123:     MaxMemory int64\n124:     \n125:     // MaxOutputSize is the maximum output size in bytes\n126:     MaxOutputSize int64\n127:     \n128:     // MaxProcesses is the maximum number of processes\n129:     MaxProcesses int\n130: }\n131: \n132: // DefaultResourceLimits returns default resource limits\n133: func DefaultResourceLimits() *ResourceLimits\n134: \n135: // Validate validates resource limits\n136: func (l *ResourceLimits) Validate() error\n137: ```\n138: \n139: ### 3. Security Options (`security.go`)\n140: \n141: ```go\n142: // SecurityOptions defines security settings for command execution\n143: type SecurityOptions struct {\n144:     // UID is the user ID to run commands as\n145:     UID int\n146:     \n147:     // GID is the group ID to run commands as\n148:     GID int\n149:     \n150:     // Capabilities is the list of allowed capabilities\n151:     Capabilities []string\n152:     \n153:     // ReadOnlyFS makes the filesystem read-only\n154:     ReadOnlyFS bool\n155:     \n156:     // NoNetwork disables network access\n157:     NoNetwork bool\n158:     \n159:     // AllowedCommands is an optional allowlist of command paths\n160:     AllowedCommands []string\n161: }\n162: \n163: // DefaultSecurityOpts returns default security options\n164: func DefaultSecurityOpts() *SecurityOptions\n165: \n166: // Validate validates security options\n167: func (o *SecurityOptions) Validate() error\n168: ```\n169: \n170: ### 4. Command Execution API (`executor.go`)\n171: \n172: ```go\n173: // Command represents a command to execute\n174: type Command struct {\n175:     // Path is the command path\n176:     Path string\n177:     \n178:     // Args are the command arguments\n179:     Args []string\n180:     \n181:     // Env is the environment variables\n182:     Env []string\n183:     \n184:     // Dir is the working directory\n185:     Dir string\n186:     \n187:     // Stdin is the standard input\n188:     Stdin io.Reader\n189:     \n190:     // Stdout is the standard output (optional, captured if nil)\n191:     Stdout io.Writer\n192:     \n193:     // Stderr is the standard error (optional, captured if nil)\n194:     Stderr io.Writer\n195: }\n196: \n197: // CommandResult represents the result of command execution\n198: type CommandResult struct {\n199:     // ExitCode is the process exit code\n200:     ExitCode int\n201:     \n202:     // Stdout is the captured standard output\n203:     Stdout []byte\n204:     \n205:     // Stderr is the captured standard error\n206:     Stderr []byte\n207:     \n208:     // Duration is the execution duration\n209:     Duration time.Duration\n210:     \n211:     // OOMKilled indicates if the process was killed due to OOM\n212:     OOMKilled bool\n213:     \n214:     // Timeout indicates if the command timed out\n215:     Timeout bool\n216: }\n217: \n218: // Run executes a command and waits for completion\n219: func (p *PicoD) Run(ctx context.Context, cmd *Command) (*CommandResult, error)\n220: \n221: // Start starts a command without waiting\n222: func (p *PicoD) Start(ctx context.Context, cmd *Command) (*Process, error)\n223: \n224: // Process represents a running process\n225: type Process struct {\n226:     // PID is the process ID\n227:     PID int\n228:     \n229:     // Wait waits for the process to complete\n230:     Wait() (*CommandResult, error)\n231:     \n232:     // Kill sends a signal to the process\n233:     Kill(signal os.Signal) error\n234: }\n235: ```\n236: \n237: ### 5. Output Streaming (`output.go`)\n238: \n239: ```go\n240: // OutputHandler handles streaming output\n241: type OutputHandler interface {\n242:     // OnStdout is called when stdout data is available\n243:     OnStdout(data []byte)\n244:     \n245:     // OnStderr is called when stderr data is available\n246:     OnStderr(data []byte)\n247:     \n248:     // OnComplete is called when execution completes\n249:     OnComplete(result *CommandResult)\n250: }\n251: \n252: // RunWithStreaming executes a command with streaming output\n253: func (p *PicoD) RunWithStreaming(ctx context.Context, cmd *Command, handler OutputHandler) (*CommandResult, error)\n254: ```\n255: \n256: ### 6. Security Validation (`security.go`)\n257: \n258: ```go\n259: // ValidateCommand validates a command for security\n260: func ValidateCommand(cmd *Command, opts *SecurityOptions) error\n261: \n262: // IsPathSafe checks if a path is within the allowed workspace\n263: func IsPathSafe(path, workDir string) bool\n264: \n265: // DropPrivileges drops privileges to the specified UID/GID\n266: func DropPrivileges(uid, gid int) error\n267: \n268: // SetResourceLimits applies resource limits to the current process\n269: func SetResourceLimits(limits *ResourceLimits) error\n270: ```\n271: \n272: ### 7. Configuration\n273: \n274: #### Environment Variables\n275: \n276: | Variable | Required | Default | Notes |\n277: |----------|----------|---------|-------|\n278: | `PICOD_WORKDIR` | No | `/tmp/picod` | Base working directory |\n279: | `PICOD_DEFAULT_TIMEOUT` | No | `30s` | Default command timeout |\n280: | `PICOD_MAX_MEMORY` | No | `128Mi` | Default memory limit |\n281: | `PICOD_MAX_CPU` | No | `1.0` | Default CPU limit |\n282: | `PICOD_MAX_OUTPUT_SIZE` | No | `10MB` | Default output size limit |\n283: | `PICOD_MAX_PROCESSES` | No | `10` | Default process limit |\n284: \n285: ### 8. Error Handling\n286: \n287: ```go\n288: // ExecutionError represents an execution error\n289: type ExecutionError struct {\n290:     // Type is the error type\n291:     Type ExecutionErrorType\n292:     \n293:     // Message is the error message\n294:     Message string\n295:     \n296:     // Underlying is the underlying error\n297:     Underlying error\n298: }\n299: \n300: type ExecutionErrorType string\n301: \n302: const (\n303:     ExecutionErrorTimeout    ExecutionErrorType = \"timeout\"\n304:     ExecutionErrorOOM        ExecutionErrorType = \"oom\"\n305:     ExecutionErrorCancelled  ExecutionErrorType = \"cancelled\"\n306:     ExecutionErrorSecurity   ExecutionErrorType = \"security\"\n307:     ExecutionErrorResource   ExecutionErrorType = \"resource\"\n308:     ExecutionErrorExec       ExecutionErrorType = \"exec\"\n309: )\n310: ```\n311: \n312: ## Impact Analysis\n313: \n314: ### Dependencies\n315: \n316: | Package | Purpose |\n317: |---------|---------|\n318: | `context` | Command cancellation and timeouts |\n319: | `os/exec` | Command execution primitives |\n320: | `syscall` | Process management and signals |\n321: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Structured logging |\n322: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | SandboxInfo type definitions |\n323: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` | Type definitions |\n324: \n325: ### Affected Components\n326: \n327: 1. **Sandbox Manager** (`pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox/`): Will use PicoD for command execution within sandboxes\n328: 2. **Workload Manager** (`pkg/workloadmanager/`): Will invoke PicoD APIs for job execution\n329: 3. **Code Interpreter** (standalone daemon): Will use PicoD execution logic\n330: 4. **Security Module**: Will configure security policies for command execution\n331: 5. **Monitoring System**: Will collect metrics from command execution\n332: \n333: ### Backward Compatibility\n334: \n335: - This is a new module with no existing API surface\n336: - No breaking changes to existing components\n337: - Configuration via environment variables and programmatic API\n338: - Existing `CodeInterpreter` CRD already references PicoD image\n339: \n340: ### Risk Assessment\n341: \n342: | Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n343: |------|------------|--------|------------|\n344: | Command injection | Low | High | Input validation, allowlist-based command selection |\n345: | Resource exhaustion | Medium | High | Enforce strict CPU/memory/time limits |\n346: | Privilege escalation | Low | Critical | Run as non-root, drop capabilities, use namespaces |\n347: | Output buffer overflow | Low | Medium | Stream large outputs, enforce size limits |\n348: | Zombie processes | Medium | Low | Proper process reaping, signal handling |\n349: \n350: ## Alternatives Considered\n351: \n352: ### Alternative 1: Use Existing Library (e.g., go-execute, bazel-remote)\n353: \n354: **Approach**: Leverage existing command execution libraries\n355: \n356: **Pros**:\n357: - Less code to maintain\n358: - Battle-tested implementations\n359: - Community support\n360: \n361: **Cons**:\n362: - May not meet specific security requirements for sandboxed execution\n363: - Additional dependency management overhead\n364: - Less control over resource limit enforcement\n365: - May not support Kubernetes-native patterns\n366: \n367: **Decision**: Implement custom solution for full control over security and limits, and better integration with AgentCube architecture.\n368: \n369: ### Alternative 2: Shell-based Execution\n370: \n371: **Approach**: Execute commands via `/bin/sh -c`\n372: \n373: **Pros**:\n374: - Simple implementation\n375: - Shell features (pipes, redirection) available\n376: - Familiar syntax\n377: \n378: **Cons**:\n379: - Security risks (shell injection attacks)\n380: - Harder to control resource limits accurately\n381: - Additional attack surface\n382: - Non-deterministic behavior across shells\n383: \n384: **Decision**: Use direct execve-style execution for better security and control.\n385: \n386: ### Alternative 3: Container-based Execution\n387: \n388: **Approach**: Spawn a new container for each command\n389: \n390: **Pros**:\n391: - Strong isolation\n392: - Built-in resource limits via cgroups\n393: - Clean environment per command\n394: \n395: **Cons**:\n396: - High overhead (container startup latency)\n397: - Requires container runtime access\n398: - Complex orchestration\n399: - Overkill for simple command execution\n400: \n401: **Decision**: Use process-level isolation with proper limits for lower latency; container isolation is handled at the sandbox pod level (AR-005).\n402: \n403: ## Testing Strategy\n404: \n405: ### Unit Tests\n406: \n407: 1. **TestPicoD_Run_Success**: Basic command execution\n408: 2. **TestPicoD_Run_Timeout**: Command exceeds timeout\n409: 3. **TestPicoD_Run_OOM**: Command exceeds memory limit\n410: 4. **TestPicoD_Run_Cancelled**: Context cancellation\n411: 5. **TestPicoD_OutputCapture**: Stdout/stderr capture\n412: 6. **TestPicoD_SecurityValidation**: Invalid commands rejected\n413: 7. **TestPicoD_ResourceLimits_Validate**: Resource limit validation\n414: 8. **TestPicoD_SecurityOpts_Validate**: Security options validation\n415: 9. **TestPicoD_WithOptions**: Functional options pattern\n416: 10. **TestPicoD_ExecutionErrorTypes**: Error type classification\n417: \n418: ### Integration Tests\n419: \n420: 1. **TestPicoD_Integration_FullLifecycle**: Full execution flow\n421: 2. **TestPicoD_Integration_Concurrent**: Multiple concurrent commands\n422: 3. **TestPicoD_Integration_ResourceLimits**: Verify limits are enforced\n423: 4. **TestPicoD_Integration_Streaming**: Output streaming functionality\n424: 5. **TestPicoD_Integration_SignalHandling**: Process signal handling\n425: \n426: ## Acceptance Criteria\n427: \n428: - [ ] `PicoD` struct implements all required methods\n429: - [ ] Resource limits are enforced (timeout, CPU, memory, output size)\n430: - [ ] Output capture works correctly (stdout, stderr, exit code)\n431: - [ ] Cancellation via context is supported\n432: - [ ] Security validations prevent dangerous operations\n433: - [ ] Streaming output is supported\n434: - [ ] All unit tests pass\n435: - [ ] Integration tests pass\n436: - [ ] Code coverage >= 80%\n437: - [ ] Documentation includes usage examples\n438: - [ ] Error types are properly classified and documented\n439: \n440: ## References\n441: \n442: - Sandbox Infrastructure: `changes/AR-012/proposal.md`\n443: - Session Storage: `changes/AR-013/proposal.md`\n444: - Valkey Storage: `changes/AR-014/proposal.md`\n445: - PicoD Spec: `code-execution/spec.md`\n446: - PicoD Design: `code-execution/design.md`\n447: - Client-Go: `deployment/client-go.md`\n\n(End of file - total 447 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-015: PicoD Command Execution API\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis proposal implements the PicoD command execution API for the `pkg/picod` module in the AgentCube project. The goal is to:\n\n1. **Secure Command Execution** - Execute commands within controlled sandbox environments with proper isolation\n2. **Resource Limit Enforcement** - Enforce CPU, memory, time, and output size limits on command execution\n3. **Output Capture and Streaming** - Capture stdout/stderr with optional streaming for long-running commands\n4. **Cancellation Support** - Enable command cancellation via context for graceful termination\n5. **Security Hardening** - Implement security validations to prevent privilege escalation and command injection\n\nThis implementation builds upon the sandbox infrastructure established in AR-012 and provides the execution engine for code interpreters and agent runtimes.\n\n## Scope\n\n**Module:** `pkg/picod`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/AR-015-proposal.md","time":{"start":1775864189916,"end":1775864189948}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775864189954,"sessionID":"ses_2863f3b4dffeWWPksoHTtGvb3O","part":{"id":"prt_d79c109b70010DL1PTYhocNLDN","messageID":"msg_d79c0edbc0011hbhimeCRbc48d","sessionID":"ses_2863f3b4dffeWWPksoHTtGvb3O","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_722ae52f581545afadd89040","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/AR-017-proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/AR-017-proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-017: PicoD JWT Middleware\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: This proposal implements JWT (JSON Web Token) authentication middleware for the PicoD HTTP daemon in the `pkg/picod` module. The goal is to:\n6: \n7: 1. **Secure API Access** - Protect PicoD HTTP endpoints with RSA-based JWT authentication\n8: 2. **Token Validation** - Validate JWT tokens signed with RSA private keys using the corresponding public key\n9: 3. **Request Authorization** - Intercept and authenticate incoming HTTP requests before allowing access to command execution APIs\n10: 4. **Flexible Configuration** - Support configuration via environment variables and command-line flags\n11: 5. **Health Endpoint Protection** - Optionally protect the health check endpoint with JWT authentication\n12: \n13: This implementation builds upon the PicoD execution infrastructure established in AR-015 and provides the security layer required for multi-tenant code interpreter deployments.\n14: \n15: ## Scope\n16: \n17: **Module:** `pkg/picod`  \n18: **Language:** Go  \n19: **Size:** S\n20: \n21: This AR covers:\n22: \n23: - **In scope:**\n24:   - JWT middleware implementation (`middleware.go`)\n25:   - JWT token validation logic (`jwt.go`)\n26:   - RSA key handling utilities (`crypto.go`)\n27:   - Configuration via environment variables and flags\n28:   - Unit tests with mocked tokens and keys\n29:   - Integration tests with real HTTP server\n30:   - Error handling and logging\n31: \n32: - **Out of scope:**\n33:   - JWT token generation (handled by external auth service)\n34:   - Token refresh mechanisms\n35:   - User/role-based authorization (only authentication)\n36:   - OAuth2 or other authentication protocols\n37:   - Session management (covered in AR-013)\n38:   - PicoD HTTP server implementation (covered in `code-execution/` specs)\n39: \n40: ## Current State Analysis\n41: \n42: ### Existing PicoD Infrastructure\n43: \n44: The current PicoD system has command execution infrastructure:\n45: \n46: 1. **PicoD Core** (`pkg/picod/picod.go`):\n47:    - Main `PicoD` struct with sandbox ID, work directory, limits, and security options\n48:    - Functional options pattern for configuration\n49:    - Structured logging with klog\n50: \n51: 2. **Command Execution** (`pkg/picod/executor.go`):\n52:    - `Run()` and `Start()` methods for command execution\n53:    - Resource limit enforcement (timeout, CPU, memory, output size)\n54:    - Output capture and streaming\n55: \n56: 3. **Security Module** (`pkg/picod/security.go`):\n57:    - Command validation and path safety checks\n58:    - Privilege dropping and capability management\n59:    - Allowlist-based command selection\n60: \n61: 4. **Configuration** (`pkg/picod/config.go`):\n62:    - Environment variable loading\n63:    - Default values for resource limits\n64: \n65: ### Gaps Identified\n66: \n67: 1. **No HTTP authentication** - PicoD HTTP daemon has no authentication layer\n68: 2. **No JWT validation** - Cannot validate JWT tokens from incoming requests\n69: 3. **No RSA key handling** - Missing utilities for loading and using RSA public keys\n70: 4. **No middleware pattern** - No HTTP middleware for request interception\n71: 5. **Health endpoint exposed** - Health check endpoint is publicly accessible\n72: \n73: ### PicoD HTTP Context\n74: \n75: Per `code-execution/design.md` and `code-execution/spec.md`:\n76: - PicoD is an HTTP daemon that runs commands inside a configurable workspace jail\n77: - Exposes health endpoint with JWT (RSA)-protected APIs\n78: - CLI flags: `-port` (default 8080), `-workspace` (default: current working directory)\n79: - Server uses `ReadHeaderTimeout` of 10 seconds\n80: - Authentication modes: `picod` (JWT required) or `none` (no auth)\n81: \n82: ### Kubernetes Client-Go Context\n83: \n84: Per `deployment/client-go.md`:\n85: - Generated Kubernetes client for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n86: - `CodeInterpreter` CRD supports `AuthMode` enum (`picod` or `none`)\n87: - Workload manager injects `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` when `AuthMode=picod`\n88: - Public key provided as base64-encoded PEM string\n89: \n90: ## Proposed Changes\n91: \n92: ### 1. JWT Middleware (`middleware.go`)\n93: \n94: ```go\n95: // JWTMiddleware is HTTP middleware that validates JWT tokens\n96: type JWTMiddleware struct {\n97:     // publicKey is the RSA public key for token validation\n98:     publicKey *rsa.PublicKey\n99:     \n100:     // skipPaths is a list of paths to skip authentication\n101:     skipPaths map[string]bool\n102:     \n103:     // logger is the structured logger\n104:     logger klog.Logger\n105: }\n106: \n107: // NewJWTMiddleware creates a new JWT middleware\n108: func NewJWTMiddleware(publicKey *rsa.PublicKey, skipPaths ...string) *JWTMiddleware\n109: \n110: // Middleware returns the HTTP middleware handler\n111: func (m *JWTMiddleware) Middleware(next http.Handler) http.Handler\n112: \n113: // extractToken extracts the JWT token from the Authorization header\n114: func (m *JWTMiddleware) extractToken(r *http.Request) (string, error)\n115: \n116: // shouldSkip checks if a path should skip authentication\n117: func (m *JWTMiddleware) shouldSkip(path string) bool\n118: ```\n119: \n120: ### 2. JWT Validation (`jwt.go`)\n121: \n122: ```go\n123: // Claims represents JWT token claims\n124: type Claims struct {\n125:     // Subject is the token subject\n126:     Sub string `json:\"sub\"`\n127:     \n128:     // Issuer is the token issuer\n129:     Iss string `json:\"iss\"`\n130:     \n131:     // Audience is the token audience\n132:     Aud string `json:\"aud\"`\n133:     \n134:     // Expiration time\n135:     Exp int64 `json:\"exp\"`\n136:     \n137:     // Issued at\n138:     Iat int64 `json:\"iat\"`\n139:     \n140:     // Custom claims for AgentCube\n141:     SandboxID string `json:\"sandbox_id,omitempty\"`\n142:     Namespace string `json:\"namespace,omitempty\"`\n143: }\n144: \n145: // Validate validates the JWT claims\n146: func (c *Claims) Validate(now time.Time) error\n147: \n148: // ParseAndValidate parses and validates a JWT token\n149: func ParseAndValidate(tokenString string, publicKey *rsa.PublicKey) (*Claims, error)\n150: \n151: // VerifySignature verifies the JWT signature\n152: func VerifySignature(tokenString string, publicKey *rsa.PublicKey) error\n153: ```\n154: \n155: ### 3. RSA Key Handling (`crypto.go`)\n156: \n157: ```go\n158: // LoadPublicKey loads an RSA public key from PEM-encoded data\n159: func LoadPublicKey(pemData []byte) (*rsa.PublicKey, error)\n160: \n161: // LoadPublicKeyFromBase64 loads an RSA public key from base64-encoded PEM\n162: func LoadPublicKeyFromBase64(base64PEM string) (*rsa.PublicKey, error)\n163: \n164: // ParsePEM parses PEM-encoded data and returns the RSA public key\n165: func ParsePEM(pemBlock *pem.Block) (*rsa.PublicKey, error)\n166: \n167: // GenerateKeyPair generates an RSA key pair for testing\n168: func GenerateKeyPair(bits int) (*rsa.PrivateKey, *rsa.PublicKey, error)\n169: ```\n170: \n171: ### 4. Configuration\n172: \n173: #### Environment Variables\n174: \n175: | Variable | Required | Default | Notes |\n176: |----------|----------|---------|-------|\n177: | `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` | Conditional | `` | Base64-encoded PEM RSA public key (required if `-auth=picod`) |\n178: | `PICOD_AUTH_MODE` | No | `none` | Authentication mode (`picod` or `none`) |\n179: | `PICOD_AUTH_SKIP_PATHS` | No | `/health` | Comma-separated list of paths to skip auth |\n180: \n181: #### Command-Line Flags\n182: \n183: ```go\n184: // Add to existing PicoD flag parsing\n185: flag.StringVar(&authMode, \"auth\", \"none\", \"Authentication mode: picod or none\")\n186: flag.StringVar(&publicKeyPEM, \"public-key\", \"\", \"RSA public key (base64-encoded PEM)\")\n187: flag.StringVar(&skipPaths, \"skip-paths\", \"/health\", \"Comma-separated paths to skip auth\")\n188: ```\n189: \n190: ### 5. Error Handling\n191: \n192: ```go\n193: // AuthError represents an authentication error\n194: type AuthError struct {\n195:     // Type is the error type\n196:     Type AuthErrorType\n197:     \n198:     // Message is the error message\n199:     Message string\n200:     \n201:     // Underlying is the underlying error\n202:     Underlying error\n203: }\n204: \n205: type AuthErrorType string\n206: \n207: const (\n208:     AuthErrorMissingToken  AuthErrorType = \"missing_token\"\n209:     AuthErrorInvalidToken  AuthErrorType = \"invalid_token\"\n210:     AuthErrorExpiredToken  AuthErrorType = \"expired_token\"\n211:     AuthErrorInvalidSig    AuthErrorType = \"invalid_signature\"\n212:     AuthErrorInvalidClaims AuthErrorType = \"invalid_claims\"\n213:     AuthErrorInternal      AuthErrorType = \"internal_error\"\n214: )\n215: \n216: // HTTPResponse returns the appropriate HTTP status code\n217: func (e *AuthError) HTTPStatus() int\n218: ```\n219: \n220: ### 6. HTTP Response Helpers\n221: \n222: ```go\n223: // WriteJSON writes a JSON response\n224: func WriteJSON(w http.ResponseWriter, status int, data interface{})\n225: \n226: // WriteError writes an error response\n227: func WriteError(w http.ResponseWriter, err error)\n228: \n229: // HealthResponse represents a health check response\n230: type HealthResponse struct {\n231:     // Status is the health status\n232:     Status string `json:\"status\"`\n233:     \n234:     // Timestamp is the current time\n235:     Timestamp time.Time `json:\"timestamp\"`\n236:     \n237:     // SandboxID is the sandbox identifier\n238:     SandboxID string `json:\"sandbox_id,omitempty\"`\n239: }\n240: ```\n241: \n242: ### 7. Integration with Existing Code\n243: \n244: ```go\n245: // SetupHTTPServer creates the HTTP server with JWT middleware\n246: func SetupHTTPServer(picod *PicoD, config *Config) (*http.Server, error) {\n247:     mux := http.NewServeMux()\n248:     \n249:     // Health endpoint (optionally protected)\n250:     mux.HandleFunc(\"/health\", handleHealth(picod))\n251:     \n252:     // Command execution endpoints (protected)\n253:     mux.HandleFunc(\"/api/v1/execute\", handleExecute(picod))\n254:     mux.HandleFunc(\"/api/v1/execute/stream\", handleExecuteStream(picod))\n255:     \n256:     // Apply JWT middleware\n257:     var handler http.Handler = mux\n258:     if config.AuthMode == \"picod\" {\n259:         publicKey, err := LoadPublicKeyFromBase64(config.PublicKeyPEM)\n260:         if err != nil {\n261:             return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to load public key: %w\", err)\n262:         }\n263:         \n264:         middleware := NewJWTMiddleware(publicKey, config.SkipPaths...)\n265:         handler = middleware.Middleware(mux)\n266:     }\n267:     \n268:     return &http.Server{\n269:         Addr:              fmt.Sprintf(\":%d\", config.Port),\n270:         Handler:           handler,\n271:         ReadHeaderTimeout: 10 * time.Second,\n272:     }, nil\n273: }\n274: ```\n275: \n276: ## Impact Analysis\n277: \n278: ### Dependencies\n279: \n280: | Package | Purpose |\n281: |---------|---------|\n282: | `crypto/rsa` | RSA signature verification |\n283: | `crypto/x509` | X.509 key parsing |\n284: | `encoding/pem` | PEM decoding |\n285: | `encoding/base64` | Base64 decoding |\n286: | `encoding/json` | JSON encoding/decoding |\n287: | `net/http` | HTTP middleware |\n288: | `strings` | String manipulation |\n289: | `time` | Time-based token validation |\n290: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Structured logging |\n291: \n292: ### Affected Components\n293: \n294: 1. **PicoD HTTP Server** (`code-execution/`): Will integrate JWT middleware into HTTP server setup\n295: 2. **Workload Manager** (`pkg/workloadmanager/`): Will configure auth mode and inject public key\n296: 3. **Code Interpreter Controller** (`pkg/controller/`): Will set `AuthMode` on `CodeInterpreter` spec\n297: 4. **Authentication Service** (external): Will generate JWT tokens for clients\n298: 5. **Client Applications**: Will include JWT tokens in `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header\n299: \n300: ### Backward Compatibility\n301: \n302: - Default auth mode is `none` (no authentication) for backward compatibility\n303: - Existing deployments without `AuthMode=picod` continue to work unchanged\n304: - Public key injection is optional and only required when `AuthMode=picod`\n305: - Health endpoint can be configured to skip authentication\n306: \n307: ### Risk Assessment\n308: \n309: | Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n310: |------|------------|--------|------------|\n311: | Token forgery | Low | Critical | Use RSA-256/512 signatures, verify with strong crypto |\n312: | Key leakage | Low | Critical | Keys managed by Kubernetes secrets, not in code |\n313: | Token replay | Medium | High | Include `iat` and `exp` claims, use short-lived tokens |\n314: | Clock skew | Medium | Medium | Allow configurable clock skew tolerance (30s) |\n315: | Performance overhead | Low | Low | RSA verification is fast (<1ms per request) |\n316: | DoS via invalid tokens | Medium | Low | Rate limiting, early rejection of malformed tokens |\n317: \n318: ## Alternatives Considered\n319: \n320: ### Alternative 1: Use Existing JWT Library (e.g., golang-jwt/jwt)\n321: \n322: **Approach**: Leverage the popular `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` library\n323: \n324: **Pros**:\n325: - Battle-tested, widely used\n326: - Handles edge cases (clock skew, token parsing)\n327: - Active community support\n328: - Supports multiple signature algorithms\n329: \n330: **Cons**:\n331: - Additional dependency\n332: - May be overkill for simple RSA verification\n333: - Larger binary size\n334: \n335: **Decision**: Use a minimal custom implementation for simplicity and control, but structure code to easily swap in `golang-jwt/jwt` if needed. The custom implementation will follow JWT standards (RFC 7519) for compatibility.\n336: \n337: ### Alternative 2: Kubernetes ServiceAccount Token\n338: \n339: **Approach**: Use Kubernetes native ServiceAccount tokens for authentication\n340: \n341: **Pros**:\n342: - Native Kubernetes integration\n343: - No additional key management\n344: - Automatic token rotation\n345: \n346: **Cons**:\n347: - Requires Kubernetes API access for validation\n348: - Tightly couples PicoD to Kubernetes\n349: - More complex validation logic\n350: - Not suitable for non-Kubernetes deployments\n351: \n352: **Decision**: Use RSA-based JWT for deployment flexibility and simpler validation. PicoD should work both inside and outside Kubernetes.\n353: \n354: ### Alternative 3: mTLS (Mutual TLS)\n355: \n356: **Approach**: Use mutual TLS for client authentication\n357: \n358: **Pros**:\n359: - Strong security (certificate-based)\n360: - Built into Go's `http.Server`\n361: - No custom token handling\n362: \n363: **Cons**:\n364: - Complex certificate management\n365: - Requires CA infrastructure\n366: - Harder to debug\n367: - Less flexible for distributed systems\n368: \n369: **Decision**: Use JWT for simpler token-based authentication. mTLS is better suited for service-to-service communication at the infrastructure level.\n370: \n371: ### Alternative 4: API Key Authentication\n372: \n373: **Approach**: Use simple API keys in headers\n374: \n375: **Pros**:\n376: - Simple implementation\n377: - Easy to debug\n378: - Low overhead\n379: \n380: **Cons**:\n381: - No standard claims structure\n382: - Harder to distribute and rotate\n383: - No built-in expiration\n384: - Less secure (symmetric keys)\n385: \n386: **Decision**: Use JWT with RSA signatures for better security, standard claims, and asymmetric key distribution.\n387: \n388: ## Testing Strategy\n389: \n390: ### Unit Tests\n391: \n392: 1. **TestJWTMiddleware_ValidToken**: Valid JWT token passes through\n393: 2. **TestJWTMiddleware_MissingToken**: Missing token returns 401\n394: 3. **TestJWTMiddleware_InvalidToken**: Malformed token returns 401\n395: 4. **TestJWTMiddleware_ExpiredToken**: Expired token returns 401\n396: 5. **TestJWTMiddleware_SkipPath**: Health endpoint skips auth\n397: 6. **TestParseAndValidate_Success**: Valid token parses claims correctly\n398: 7. **TestParseAndValidate_InvalidSignature**: Tampered token fails verification\n399: 8. **TestClaims_Validate_Expired**: Expired claims fail validation\n400: 9. **TestClaims_Validate_Future**: Not-yet-valid claims fail validation\n401: 10. **TestLoadPublicKeyFromBase64**: Correctly loads base64-encoded PEM key\n402: 11. **TestLoadPublicKey_InvalidPEM**: Invalid PEM returns error\n403: 12. **TestAuthError_HTTPStatus**: Error types map to correct HTTP codes\n404: \n405: ### Integration Tests\n406: \n407: 1. **TestJWTMiddleware_Integration_FullFlow**: Full HTTP request with valid token\n408: 2. **TestJWTMiddleware_Integration_MultipleRequests**: Multiple concurrent requests\n409: 3. **TestJWTMiddleware_Integration_KeyRotation**: Server handles key change (restart)\n410: 4. **TestJWTMiddleware_Integration_HealthEndpoint**: Health endpoint with/without auth\n411: \n412: ### Test Fixtures\n413: \n414: ```go\n415: // generateTestToken creates a signed JWT token for testing\n416: func generateTestToken(privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey, claims *Claims) (string, error)\n417: \n418: // testClaims returns standard test claims\n419: func testClaims() *Claims {\n420:     return &Claims{\n421:         Sub:       \"test-user\",\n422:         Iss:       \"test-issuer\",\n423:         Aud:       \"picod\",\n424:         Exp:       time.Now().Add(1 * time.Hour).Unix(),\n425:         Iat:       time.Now().Unix(),\n426:         SandboxID: \"test-sandbox\",\n427:         Namespace: \"default\",\n428:     }\n429: }\n430: \n431: // generateTestKeyPair creates a test RSA key pair\n432: func generateTestKeyPair() (*rsa.PrivateKey, *rsa.PublicKey, error)\n433: ```\n434: \n435: ## Acceptance Criteria\n436: \n437: - [ ] JWT middleware correctly validates tokens\n438: - [ ] Invalid/missing tokens return 401 Unauthorized\n439: - [ ] Expired tokens are rejected\n440: - [ ] Signature verification works with RSA public key\n441: - [ ] Configurable skip paths work correctly\n442: - [ ] Health endpoint can be protected or public\n443: - [ ] Claims are correctly parsed and validated\n444: - [ ] Error types map to appropriate HTTP status codes\n445: - [ ] All unit tests pass\n446: - [ ] Integration tests pass\n447: - [ ] Code coverage >= 80%\n448: - [ ] Documentation includes usage examples\n449: - [ ] Compatible with standard JWT libraries (e.g., PyJWT, jose)\n450: \n451: ## References\n452: \n453: - AR-015: PicoD Command Execution API\n454: - AR-013: Session Storage\n455: - `code-execution/spec.md`: PicoD Specification\n456: - `code-execution/design.md`: PicoD Design\n457: - `deployment/client-go.md`: Kubernetes Client-Go\n458: - `deployment/spec.md`: Deployment Configuration\n459: - RFC 7519: JSON Web Token (JWT)\n460: - RFC 7515: JSON Web Signature (JWS)\n\n(End of file - total 460 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-017: PicoD JWT Middleware\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis proposal implements JWT (JSON Web Token) authentication middleware for the PicoD HTTP daemon in the `pkg/picod` module. The goal is to:\n\n1. **Secure API Access** - Protect PicoD HTTP endpoints with RSA-based JWT authentication\n2. **Token Validation** - Validate JWT tokens signed with RSA private keys using the corresponding public key\n3. **Request Authorization** - Intercept and authenticate incoming HTTP requests before allowing access to command execution APIs\n4. **Flexible Configuration** - Support configuration via environment variables and command-line flags\n5. **Health Endpoint Protection** - Optionally protect the health check endpoint with JWT authentication\n\nThis implementation builds upon the PicoD execution infrastructure established in AR-015 and provides the security layer required for multi-tenant code interpreter deployments.\n\n## Scope\n\n**Module:** `pkg/picod`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/AR-017-proposal.md","time":{"start":1775864189919,"end":1775864189951}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775864189957,"sessionID":"ses_2863f3b4dffeWWPksoHTtGvb3O","part":{"id":"prt_d79c10f53001o8pFl1eTRCMOxS","messageID":"msg_d79c0edbc0011hbhimeCRbc48d","sessionID":"ses_2863f3b4dffeWWPksoHTtGvb3O","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_392fcbe6f96c435ea0902989","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/project.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/project.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube — OpenSpec Project Context\n2: \n3: > Source: [github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube](https://github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube)\n4: > Generated: 2026-03-21 (from source tree reverse-engineering)\n5: \n6: ## Purpose\n7: \n8: AgentCube is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents.\n9: It provisions isolated sandbox pods on demand, routes HTTP traffic to them through\n10: session-aware proxies, and manages their lifecycle (creation, expiry, idle cleanup).\n11: \n12: ## Tech Stack\n13: \n14: | Layer | Technology |\n15: |-------|-----------|\n16: | Language (server) | Go 1.24, module `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` |\n17: | Language (CLI/SDK) | Python ≥3.10 |\n18: | HTTP framework | Gin (Go), Typer (Python CLI), FastAPI (example) |\n19: | Kubernetes | CRDs (`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`), controller-runtime, `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` |\n20: | Storage | Redis (go-redis/v9), Valkey (valkey-go) |\n21: | Auth | JWT RS256 (golang-jwt/v5), K8s TokenReview |\n22: | Packaging | Helm 3, multi-stage Docker, GitHub Actions CI/CD |\n23: | Docs | Docusaurus 3.x |\n24: \n25: ## Architecture\n26: \n27: ```\n28: Client / SDK / CLI\n29:   → Router (Deployment :8080)\n30:      ↔ Redis/Valkey (session store)\n31:      → WorkloadManager (Service :8080)\n32:         ↔ Redis/Valkey\n33:         → K8s API: CRDs, Sandbox, Pod, Secret, TokenReview\n34:   Sandbox Pods (with optional PicoD daemon)\n35:   Agentd (idle cleanup controller)\n36:   Optional: Volcano vc-agent-scheduler\n37: ```\n38: \n39: ## Conventions\n40: \n41: - Go packages under `pkg/`, binaries under `cmd/`\n42: - Python CLI at `cmd/cli/`, SDK at `sdk-python/`\n43: - JSON tags use camelCase; Go structs use PascalCase\n44: - K8s resources use `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` API group\n45: - Normative language: SHALL = mandatory, SHOULD = recommended, MAY = optional\n\n(End of file - total 45 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube — OpenSpec Project Context\n\n> Source: [github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube](https://github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube)\n> Generated: 2026-03-21 (from source tree reverse-engineering)\n\n## Purpose\n\nAgentCube is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents.\nIt provisions isolated sandbox pods on demand, routes HTTP traffic to them through\nsession-aware proxies, and manages their lifecycle (creation, expiry, idle cleanup).\n\n## Tech Stack\n\n| Layer | Technology |\n|-------|-----------|\n| Language (server) | Go 1.24, module `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` |\n| Language (CLI/SDK) | Python ≥3.10 |\n| HTTP framework | Gin (Go), Typer (Python CLI), FastAPI (example) |\n| Kubernetes | CRDs (`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`), controller-runtime, `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` |\n| Storage | Redis (go-redis/v9), Valkey (valkey-go) |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/project.md","time":{"start":1775864189921,"end":1775864189956}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775864189962,"sessionID":"ses_2863f3b4dffeWWPksoHTtGvb3O","part":{"id":"prt_d79c0faaa0010uIbamDRlcEQor","messageID":"msg_d79c0edbc0011hbhimeCRbc48d","sessionID":"ses_2863f3b4dffeWWPksoHTtGvb3O","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_a74f7f4acbd542be9df1e800","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/cmd/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/cmd/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Design: AR-019 CLI Binary Entry Points\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This document describes the technical implementation for 4 CLI binaries in the agentcube project. These tools provide command-line interfaces for managing agentcube resources and interacting with the Kubernetes API.\n6: \n7: ## Architecture\n8: \n9: ### Binary Structure\n10: \n11: ```\n12: cmd/\n13: ├── agentd/                      # Kubernetes controller (existing)\n14: │   └── main.go\n15: ├── agentcube/                   # Main CLI - resource management\n16: │   └── main.go\n17: ├── agentcube-admin/             # Admin CLI - cluster administration\n18: │   └── main.go\n19: ├── agentcube-shell/             # Interactive shell - sandbox access\n20: │   └── main.go\n21: └── agentcube-proxy/             # API proxy - local port forwarding\n22:     └── main.go\n23: ```\n24: \n25: ### Module Dependencies\n26: \n27: - **client-go**: `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go`\n28:   - Typed clients for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n29:   - Informers for watching resources\n30:   - Listers for cached read access\n31: - **controller-runtime**: Shared utilities for config, logging\n32: - **cobra**: CLI framework (all binaries)\n33: \n34: ## Data Structures\n35: \n36: ### agentcube (Main CLI)\n37: \n38: ```go\n39: type CLI struct {\n40:     clientset     versioned.Interface\n41:     informerFactory informers.SharedInformerFactory\n42:     namespace     string\n43:     outputFormat  string\n44: }\n45: \n46: type SandboxOptions struct {\n47:     Name           string\n48:     Namespace      string\n49:     RuntimeType    string\n50:     CPURequest     string\n51:     MemoryRequest  string\n52:     Labels         map[string]string\n53:     Annotations    map[string]string\n54:     Timeout        time.Duration\n55: }\n56: \n57: type RuntimeOptions struct {\n58:     Name          string\n59:     Namespace     string\n60:     Spec          runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec\n61:     Timeout       time.Duration\n62: }\n63: ```\n64: \n65: ### agentcube-admin (Admin CLI)\n66: \n67: ```go\n68: type AdminCLI struct {\n69:     clientset     versioned.Interface\n70:     kubeClient    kubernetes.Interface\n71:     config        *rest.Config\n72: }\n73: \n74: type QuotaConfig struct {\n75:     Namespace      string\n76:     DefaultCPU     string\n77:     DefaultMemory  string\n78:     MaxCPU         string\n79:     MaxMemory      string\n80:     MaxSandboxes   int64\n81: }\n82: \n83: type ClusterConfig struct {\n84:     AllowedRuntimes []string\n85:     DefaultNamespace string\n86:     EnableMonitoring bool\n87: }\n88: ```\n89: \n90: ### agentcube-shell (Interactive Shell)\n91: \n92: ```go\n93: type Shell struct {\n94:     clientset     versioned.Interface\n95:     kubeClient    kubernetes.Interface\n96:     restClient    *rest.RESTClient\n97:     sandboxName   string\n98:     namespace     string\n99:     shellType     string  // bash, sh, zsh\n100: }\n101: \n102: type SessionConfig struct {\n103:     Timeout        time.Duration\n104:     IdleTimeout    time.Duration\n105:     HistoryFile    string\n106:     MaxHistory     int\n107: }\n108: ```\n109: \n110: ### agentcube-proxy (API Proxy)\n111: \n112: ```go\n113: type Proxy struct {\n114:     clientset     versioned.Interface\n115:     localPort     int\n116:     targetPort    int\n117:     namespace     string\n118:     resourceType  string  // agentruntime, codeinterpreter\n119:     resourceName  string\n120: }\n121: \n122: type ProxyConfig struct {\n123:     ListenAddress  string\n124:     ListenPort     int\n125:     TLS            bool\n126:     TLSCert        string\n127:     TLSKey         string\n128:     AuthToken      string\n129: }\n130: ```\n131: \n132: ## API Contracts\n133: \n134: ### agentcube Commands\n135: \n136: ```bash\n137: # Sandbox management\n138: agentcube sandbox create <name> [--runtime=<type>] [--namespace=<ns>] [--cpu=<req>] [--memory=<req>]\n139: agentcube sandbox get <name> [--namespace=<ns>] [-o=json|yaml]\n140: agentcube sandbox list [--namespace=<ns>] [-l=<labels>]\n141: agentcube sandbox delete <name> [--namespace=<ns>] [--force]\n142: agentcube sandbox watch <name> [--namespace=<ns>] [--timeout=<duration>]\n143: \n144: # Runtime management\n145: agentcube runtime create <name> --spec=<file> [--namespace=<ns>]\n146: agentcube runtime get <name> [--namespace=<ns>] [-o=json|yaml]\n147: agentcube runtime list [--namespace=<ns>]\n148: agentcube runtime update <name> --spec=<file>\n149: agentcube runtime delete <name> [--namespace=<ns>]\n150: \n151: # Utility\n152: agentcube version\n153: agentcube completion <bash|zsh|fish>\n154: agentcube config view\n155: agentcube config set <key>=<value>\n156: ```\n157: \n158: ### agentcube-admin Commands\n159: \n160: ```bash\n161: # Quota management\n162: agentcube-admin quota set <namespace> --cpu=<default> --memory=<default> --max-cpu=<max> --max-memory=<max>\n163: agentcube-admin quota get <namespace>\n164: agentcube-admin quota list\n165: \n166: # Cluster configuration\n167: agentcube-admin config get\n168: agentcube-admin config update --file=<config>\n169: \n170: # Health & diagnostics\n171: agentcube-admin health check\n172: agentcube-admin health report [-o=json|yaml]\n173: \n174: # Cleanup\n175: agentcube-admin cleanup idle [--older-than=<duration>]\n176: agentcube-admin cleanup failed [--namespace=<ns>]\n177: ```\n178: \n179: ### agentcube-shell Commands\n180: \n181: ```bash\n182: # Interactive access\n183: agentcube-shell connect <sandbox-name> [--namespace=<ns>] [--shell=<type>]\n184: agentcube-shell exec <sandbox-name> <command> [--namespace=<ns>]\n185: agentcube-shell cp <sandbox-name>:<src> <dst> [--namespace=<ns>]\n186: agentcube-shell port-forward <sandbox-name> <local-port>:<remote-port>\n187: \n188: # Session management\n189: agentcube-shell sessions list\n190: agentcube-shell sessions kill <session-id>\n191: ```\n192: \n193: ### agentcube-proxy Commands\n194: \n195: ```bash\n196: # API proxy\n197: agentcube-proxy start --resource=<type>/<name> --port=<local-port> [--namespace=<ns>]\n198: agentcube-proxy start --api-server --port=<local-port>\n199: \n200: # Status\n201: agentcube-proxy status\n202: agentcube-proxy stop\n203: ```\n204: \n205: ## Implementation Details\n206: \n207: ### Shared Libraries\n208: \n209: ```go\n210: // pkg/cliutil/config.go\n211: type ClientConfig struct {\n212:     Kubeconfig   string\n213:     Context      string\n214:     Namespace    string\n215:     APIServer    string\n216:     Token        string\n217:     Timeout      time.Duration\n218: }\n219: \n220: func LoadConfig() (*ClientConfig, error)\n221: func (c *ClientConfig) GetClientset() (versioned.Interface, error)\n222: func (c *ClientConfig) GetInformerFactory() (informers.SharedInformerFactory, error)\n223: \n224: // pkg/cliutil/output.go\n225: func PrintObject(obj runtime.Object, format string) error\n226: func PrintTable(rows [][]string, headers []string) error\n227: func PrintStatus(status string, format string) error\n228: \n229: // pkg/cliutil/validation.go\n230: func ValidateSandboxName(name string) error\n231: func ValidateRuntimeType(rt string, allowed []string) error\n232: func ValidateResourceQuantity(q string) error\n233: ```\n234: \n235: ### agentcube - Main CLI\n236: \n237: ```go\n238: // cmd/agentcube/main.go\n239: func main() {\n240:     rootCmd := &cobra.Command{\n241:         Use:   \"agentcube\",\n242:         Short: \"AgentCube CLI for managing agent runtimes and sandboxes\",\n243:     }\n244:     \n245:     rootCmd.PersistentFlags().String(\"kubeconfig\", \"\", \"path to kubeconfig\")\n246:     rootCmd.PersistentFlags().String(\"namespace\", \"default\", \"namespace\")\n247:     rootCmd.PersistentFlags().StringP(\"output\", \"o\", \"table\", \"output format\")\n248:     \n249:     rootCmd.AddCommand(sandboxCmd, runtimeCmd, configCmd, versionCmd)\n250:     \n251:     if err := rootCmd.Execute(); err != nil {\n252:         os.Exit(1)\n253:     }\n254: }\n255: \n256: // cmd/agentcube/sandbox.go\n257: func newSandboxCreateCmd() *cobra.Command {\n258:     opts := &SandboxOptions{}\n259:     cmd := &cobra.Command{\n260:         Use:   \"create <name>\",\n261:         Args:  cobra.ExactArgs(1),\n262:         RunE: func(cmd *cobra.Command, args []string) error {\n263:             opts.Name = args[0]\n264:             return runSandboxCreate(opts)\n265:         },\n266:     }\n267:     cmd.Flags().StringVar(&opts.RuntimeType, \"runtime\", \"jupyter\", \"runtime type\")\n268:     cmd.Flags().StringVar(&opts.CPURequest, \"cpu\", \"100m\", \"CPU request\")\n269:     cmd.Flags().StringVar(&opts.MemoryRequest, \"memory\", \"256Mi\", \"memory request\")\n270:     return cmd\n271: }\n272: \n273: func runSandboxCreate(opts *SandboxOptions) error {\n274:     cfg, err := cliutil.LoadConfig()\n275:     if err != nil {\n276:         return err\n277:     }\n278:     \n279:     clientset, err := cfg.GetClientset()\n280:     if err != nil {\n281:         return err\n282:     }\n283:     \n284:     // Construct CodeInterpreter object\n285:     ci := &runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter{\n286:         ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n287:             Name:      opts.Name,\n288:             Namespace: opts.Namespace,\n289:             Labels:    opts.Labels,\n290:         },\n291:         Spec: runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreterSpec{\n292:             RuntimeType: opts.RuntimeType,\n293:             Resources: v1.ResourceRequirements{\n294:                 Requests: v1.ResourceList{\n295:                     v1.ResourceCPU:    resource.MustParse(opts.CPURequest),\n296:                     v1.ResourceMemory: resource.MustParse(opts.MemoryRequest),\n297:                 },\n298:             },\n299:         },\n300:     }\n301:     \n302:     result, err := clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(opts.Namespace).Create(\n303:         cmd.Context(), ci, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n304:     if err != nil {\n305:         return err\n306:     }\n307:     \n308:     return cliutil.PrintObject(result, cfg.OutputFormat)\n309: }\n310: ```\n311: \n312: ### agentcube-admin - Admin CLI\n313: \n314: ```go\n315: // cmd/agentcube-admin/main.go\n316: func main() {\n317:     rootCmd := &cobra.Command{\n318:         Use:   \"agentcube-admin\",\n319:         Short: \"AgentCube Admin CLI for cluster administration\",\n320:     }\n321:     \n322:     rootCmd.PersistentFlags().String(\"kubeconfig\", \"\", \"path to kubeconfig\")\n323:     rootCmd.PersistentFlags().String(\"context\", \"\", \"kubeconfig context\")\n324:     \n325:     rootCmd.AddCommand(quotaCmd, configCmd, healthCmd, cleanupCmd)\n326:     \n327:     if err := rootCmd.Execute(); err != nil {\n328:         os.Exit(1)\n329:     }\n330: }\n331: \n332: // cmd/agentcube-admin/quota.go\n333: func runQuotaSet(namespace string, cfg *QuotaConfig) error {\n334:     clientset, kubeClient, err := getAdminClients()\n335:     if err != nil {\n336:         return err\n337:     }\n338:     \n339:     // Check if namespace exists\n340:     _, err = kubeClient.CoreV1().Namespaces().Get(context.Background(), namespace, metav1.GetOptions{})\n341:     if err != nil {\n342:         return fmt.Errorf(\"namespace %q not found: %w\", namespace, err)\n343:     }\n344:     \n345:     // Create/update resource quota\n346:     quota := &v1.ResourceQuota{\n347:         ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n348:             Name:      \"agentcube-quota\",\n349:             Namespace: namespace,\n350:         },\n351:         Spec: v1.ResourceQuotaSpec{\n352:             Hard: v1.ResourceList{\n353:                 v1.ResourceRequestsCPU:    resource.MustParse(cfg.DefaultCPU),\n354:                 v1.ResourceRequestsMemory: resource.MustParse(cfg.DefaultMemory),\n355:                 v1.ResourceLimitsCPU:      resource.MustParse(cfg.MaxCPU),\n356:                 v1.ResourceLimitsMemory:   resource.MustParse(cfg.MaxMemory),\n357:             },\n358:         },\n359:     }\n360:     \n361:     _, err = kubeClient.CoreV1().ResourceQuotas(namespace).Create(\n362:         context.Background(), quota, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n363:     if apierrors.IsAlreadyExists(err) {\n364:         _, err = kubeClient.CoreV1().ResourceQuotas(namespace).Update(\n365:             context.Background(), quota, metav1.UpdateOptions{})\n366:     }\n367:     \n368:     return err\n369: }\n370: ```\n371: \n372: ### agentcube-shell - Interactive Shell\n373: \n374: ```go\n375: // cmd/agentcube-shell/main.go\n376: func main() {\n377:     rootCmd := &cobra.Command{\n378:         Use:   \"agentcube-shell\",\n379:         Short: \"AgentCube Interactive Shell for sandbox access\",\n380:     }\n381:     \n382:     rootCmd.PersistentFlags().String(\"kubeconfig\", \"\", \"path to kubeconfig\")\n383:     rootCmd.PersistentFlags().String(\"namespace\", \"default\", \"namespace\")\n384:     rootCmd.PersistentFlags().Duration(\"timeout\", 30*time.Minute, \"session timeout\")\n385:     \n386:     rootCmd.AddCommand(connectCmd, execCmd, cpCmd, portForwardCmd, sessionsCmd)\n387:     \n388:     if err := rootCmd.Execute(); err != nil {\n389:         os.Exit(1)\n390:     }\n391: }\n392: \n393: // cmd/agentcube-shell/connect.go\n394: func runConnect(sandboxName string, cfg *SessionConfig) error {\n395:     clientset, kubeClient, restConfig := getShellClients()\n396:     \n397:     // Get sandbox\n398:     ci, err := clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(cfg.Namespace).Get(\n399:         context.Background(), sandboxName, metav1.GetOptions{})\n400:     if err != nil {\n401:         return err\n402:     }\n403:     \n404:     if ci.Status.Phase != runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreterRunning {\n405:         return fmt.Errorf(\"sandbox is not running (phase: %s)\", ci.Status.Phase)\n406:     }\n407:     \n408:     // Get pod name from status\n409:     podName := ci.Status.PodName\n410:     if podName == \"\" {\n411:         return fmt.Errorf(\"sandbox pod name not available\")\n412:     }\n413:     \n414:     // Establish SPDY connection for exec\n415:     req := kubeClient.CoreV1().RESTClient().Post().\n416:         Resource(\"pods\").\n417:         Name(podName).\n418:         Namespace(cfg.Namespace).\n419:         SubResource(\"exec\").\n420:         Param(\"container\", \"sandbox\").\n421:         Param(\"stdin\", \"true\").\n422:         Param(\"stdout\", \"true\").\n423:         Param(\"stderr\", \"true\").\n424:         Param(\"tty\", \"true\").\n425:         Param(\"command\", cfg.ShellType)\n426:     \n427:     executor, err := remotecommand.NewSPDYExecutor(restConfig, \"POST\", req.URL())\n428:     if err != nil {\n429:         return err\n430:     }\n431:     \n432:     // Attach terminal\n433:     return executor.StreamWithContext(context.Background(), remotecommand.StreamOptions{\n434:         Stdin:  os.Stdin,\n435:         Stdout: os.Stdout,\n436:         Stderr: os.Stderr,\n437:         Tty:    true,\n438:     })\n439: }\n440: ```\n441: \n442: ### agentcube-proxy - API Proxy\n443: \n444: ```go\n445: // cmd/agentcube-proxy/main.go\n446: func main() {\n447:     rootCmd := &cobra.Command{\n448:         Use:   \"agentcube-proxy\",\n449:         Short: \"AgentCube API Proxy for local port forwarding\",\n450:     }\n451:     \n452:     rootCmd.PersistentFlags().String(\"kubeconfig\", \"\", \"path to kubeconfig\")\n453:     rootCmd.PersistentFlags().String(\"listen\", \"127.0.0.1\", \"listen address\")\n454:     rootCmd.PersistentFlags().Int(\"port\", 8080, \"listen port\")\n455:     \n456:     rootCmd.AddCommand(startCmd, statusCmd, stopCmd)\n457:     \n458:     if err := rootCmd.Execute(); err != nil {\n459:         os.Exit(1)\n460:     }\n461: }\n462: \n463: // cmd/agentcube-proxy/start.go\n464: func runProxy(opts *ProxyConfig) error {\n465:     clientset, restConfig := getProxyClients()\n466:     \n467:     // Build transport with auth\n468:     transport, err := rest.TransportFor(restConfig)\n469:     if err != nil {\n470:         return err\n471:     }\n472:     \n473:     // Create reverse proxy\n474:     targetURL := restConfig.Host\n475:     proxy := httputil.NewSingleHostReverseProxy(targetURL)\n476:     proxy.Transport = transport\n477:     \n478:     // Add authentication header\n479:     baseHandler := http.HandlerFunc(func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n480:         if opts.AuthToken != \"\" {\n481:             if token := r.Header.Get(\"Authorization\"); token != \"Bearer \"+opts.AuthToken {\n482:                 http.Error(w, \"unauthorized\", http.StatusUnauthorized)\n483:                 return\n484:             }\n485:         }\n486:         proxy.ServeHTTP(w, r)\n487:     })\n488:     \n489:     server := &http.Server{\n490:         Addr:    fmt.Sprintf(\"%s:%d\", opts.ListenAddress, opts.ListenPort),\n491:         Handler: baseHandler,\n492:     }\n493:     \n494:     if opts.TLS {\n495:         return server.ListenAndServeTLS(opts.TLSCert, opts.TLSKey)\n496:     }\n497:     \n498:     return server.ListenAndServe()\n499: }\n500: ```\n501: \n502: ## Error Handling\n503: \n504: ### Error Categories\n505: \n506: ```go\n507: // pkg/cliutil/errors.go\n508: type CLIError struct {\n509:     Code    string\n510:     Message string\n511:     Err     error\n512: }\n513: \n514: func (e *CLIError) Error() string {\n515:     return fmt.Sprintf(\"[%s] %s: %v\", e.Code, e.Message, e.Err)\n516: }\n517: \n518: // Error codes\n519: const (\n520:     ErrConfigNotFound   = \"CONFIG_NOT_FOUND\"\n521:     ErrAuthFailed       = \"AUTH_FAILED\"\n522:     ErrResourceNotFound = \"RESOURCE_NOT_FOUND\"\n523:     ErrResourceExists   = \"RESOURCE_EXISTS\"\n524:     ErrInvalidInput     = \"INVALID_INPUT\"\n525:     ErrTimeout          = \"TIMEOUT\"\n526:     ErrInternal         = \"INTERNAL\"\n527: )\n528: \n529: func NewCLIError(code, msg string, err error) *CLIError {\n530:     return &CLIError{Code: code, Message: msg, Err: err}\n531: }\n532: \n533: func WrapError(err error, msg string) *CLIError {\n534:     return &CLIError{Code: ErrInternal, Message: msg, Err: err}\n535: }\n536: ```\n537: \n538: ### Error Handling Strategy\n539: \n540: 1. **Configuration errors**: Clear message + path to fix\n541: 2. **API errors**: Show resource name, namespace, and API response\n542: 3. **Validation errors**: List all validation failures\n543: 4. **Timeout errors**: Suggest increasing timeout or checking resource status\n544: 5. **Internal errors**: Include correlation ID for debugging\n545: \n546: ```go\n547: func handleError(err error) {\n548:     var cliErr *CLIError\n549:     if errors.As(err, &cliErr) {\n550:         fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"Error %s: %s\\n\", cliErr.Code, cliErr.Message)\n551:         if cliErr.Err != nil {\n552:             fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"Caused by: %v\\n\", cliErr.Err)\n553:         }\n554:         os.Exit(1)\n555:     }\n556:     \n557:     // Handle Kubernetes API errors\n558:     if apierrors.IsNotFound(err) {\n559:         fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"Error: resource not found\\n\")\n560:     } else if apierrors.IsAlreadyExists(err) {\n561:         fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"Error: resource already exists\\n\")\n562:     } else if apierrors.IsForbidden(err) {\n563:         fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"Error: permission denied\\n\")\n564:     } else {\n565:         fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"Error: %v\\n\", err)\n566:     }\n567:     os.Exit(1)\n568: }\n569: ```\n570: \n571: ## Testing Strategy\n572: \n573: ### Unit Tests\n574: \n575: ```go\n576: // cmd/agentcube/sandbox_test.go\n577: func TestRunSandboxCreate(t *testing.T) {\n578:     tests := []struct {\n579:         name    string\n580:         opts    *SandboxOptions\n581:         wantErr bool\n582:     }{\n583:         {\n584:             name: \"valid options\",\n585:             opts: &SandboxOptions{\n586:                 Name:        \"test-sandbox\",\n587:                 Namespace:   \"default\",\n588:                 RuntimeType: \"jupyter\",\n589:             },\n590:             wantErr: false,\n591:         },\n592:         {\n593:             name: \"invalid runtime type\",\n594:             opts: &SandboxOptions{\n595:                 Name:        \"test-sandbox\",\n596:                 RuntimeType: \"invalid\",\n597:             },\n598:             wantErr: true,\n599:         },\n600:     }\n601:     \n602:     for _, tt := range tests {\n603:         t.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n604:             // Use fake clientset\n605:             clientset := fake.NewSimpleClientset()\n606:             err := runSandboxCreateWithClient(tt.opts, clientset)\n607:             if (err != nil) != tt.wantErr {\n608:                 t.Errorf(\"runSandboxCreate() error = %v, wantErr %v\", err, tt.wantErr)\n609:             }\n610:         })\n611:     }\n612: }\n613: ```\n614: \n615: ### Integration Tests\n616: \n617: ```go\n618: // test/integration/cli_test.go\n619: func TestSandboxCreateGetDelete(t *testing.T) {\n620:     // Skip if no cluster available\n621:     if testing.Short() {\n622:         t.Skip(\"skipping integration test\")\n623:     }\n624:     \n625:     // Create test namespace\n626:     ns := createTestNamespace(t)\n627:     defer deleteTestNamespace(t, ns)\n628:     \n629:     // Create sandbox via CLI\n630:     cmd := exec.Command(\"agentcube\", \"sandbox\", \"create\", \"test-sandbox\",\n631:         \"--namespace\", ns, \"--runtime\", \"jupyter\")\n632:     output, err := cmd.CombinedOutput()\n633:     if err != nil {\n634:         t.Fatalf(\"sandbox create failed: %v\\n%s\", err, output)\n635:     }\n636:     \n637:     // Get sandbox\n638:     cmd = exec.Command(\"agentcube\", \"sandbox\", \"get\", \"test-sandbox\",\n639:         \"--namespace\", ns, \"-o\", \"json\")\n640:     output, err = cmd.CombinedOutput()\n641:     if err != nil {\n642:         t.Fatalf(\"sandbox get failed: %v\\n%s\", err, output)\n643:     }\n644:     \n645:     // Delete sandbox\n646:     cmd = exec.Command(\"agentcube\", \"sandbox\", \"delete\", \"test-sandbox\",\n647:         \"--namespace\", ns)\n648:     output, err = cmd.CombinedOutput()\n649:     if err != nil {\n650:         t.Fatalf(\"sandbox delete failed: %v\\n%s\", err, output)\n651:     }\n652: }\n653: ```\n654: \n655: ### E2E Tests\n656: \n657: ```go\n658: // test/e2e/cli_e2e_test.go\n659: func TestFullWorkflow(t *testing.T) {\n660:     // Full workflow: create -> verify -> exec -> delete\n661:     ctx := context.Background()\n662:     \n663:     // Create\n664:     err := runAgentcube(ctx, \"sandbox\", \"create\", \"e2e-test\", \"--runtime\", \"python\")\n665:     require.NoError(t, err)\n666:     \n667:     // Wait for running\n668:     require.NoError(t, waitForSandboxRunning(ctx, \"e2e-test\"))\n669:     \n670:     // Execute command\n671:     output, err := runAgentcubeShell(ctx, \"exec\", \"e2e-test\", \"python\", \"-c\", \"print('hello')\")\n672:     require.NoError(t, err)\n673:     assert.Contains(t, output, \"hello\")\n674:     \n675:     // Cleanup\n676:     runAgentcube(ctx, \"sandbox\", \"delete\", \"e2e-test\", \"--force\")\n677: }\n678: ```\n679: \n680: ## File Index\n681: \n682: | Path | Role |\n683: |------|------|\n684: | `cmd/agentcube/main.go` | Main CLI entry point |\n685: | `cmd/agentcube/sandbox.go` | Sandbox subcommands |\n686: | `cmd/agentcube/runtime.go` | Runtime subcommands |\n687: | `cmd/agentcube/config.go` | Configuration commands |\n688: | `cmd/agentcube-admin/main.go` | Admin CLI entry point |\n689: | `cmd/agentcube-admin/quota.go` | Quota management |\n690: | `cmd/agentcube-admin/health.go` | Health checks |\n691: | `cmd/agentcube-admin/cleanup.go` | Cleanup operations |\n692: | `cmd/agentcube-shell/main.go` | Shell CLI entry point |\n693: | `cmd/agentcube-shell/connect.go` | Interactive connect |\n694: | `cmd/agentcube-shell/exec.go` | Remote exec |\n695: | `cmd/agentcube-proxy/main.go` | Proxy CLI entry point |\n696: | `cmd/agentcube-proxy/start.go` | Proxy server |\n697: | `pkg/cliutil/config.go` | Shared config loading |\n698: | `pkg/cliutil/output.go` | Output formatting |\n699: | `pkg/cliutil/errors.go` | Error types |\n700: | `pkg/cliutil/validation.go` | Input validation |\n701: | `test/integration/cli_test.go` | Integration tests |\n702: | `test/e2e/cli_e2e_test.go` | E2E tests |\n703: \n704: ## Build & Installation\n705: \n706: ### Makefile Targets\n707: \n708: ```makefile\n709: # Build all binaries\n710: build-cli:\n711:     go build -o bin/agentcube ./cmd/agentcube\n712:     go build -o bin/agentcube-admin ./cmd/agentcube-admin\n713:     go build -o bin/agentcube-shell ./cmd/agentcube-shell\n714:     go build -o bin/agentcube-proxy ./cmd/agentcube-proxy\n715: \n716: # Install to GOPATH\n717: install-cli:\n718:     go install ./cmd/agentcube\n719:     go install ./cmd/agentcube-admin\n720:     go install ./cmd/agentcube-shell\n721:     go install ./cmd/agentcube-proxy\n722: \n723: # Cross-compile\n724: build-all-platforms:\n725:     GOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64 go build -o bin/linux/amd64/agentcube ./cmd/agentcube\n726:     GOOS=darwin GOARCH=amd64 go build -o bin/darwin/amd64/agentcube ./cmd/agentcube\n727:     GOOS=windows GOARCH=amd64 go build -o bin/windows/amd64/agentcube.exe ./cmd/agentcube\n728: ```\n729: \n730: ### Release Artifacts\n731: \n732: - `agentcube-linux-amd64`, `agentcube-darwin-amd64`, `agentcube-windows-amd64.exe`\n733: - `agentcube-admin-linux-amd64`, etc.\n734: - `agentcube-shell-linux-amd64`, etc.\n735: - `agentcube-proxy-linux-amd64`, etc.\n736: - Shell completion scripts: `agentcube-completion.bash`, `agentcube-completion.zsh`\n\n(End of file - total 736 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Design: AR-019 CLI Binary Entry Points\n\n## Overview\n\nThis document describes the technical implementation for 4 CLI binaries in the agentcube project. These tools provide command-line interfaces for managing agentcube resources and interacting with the Kubernetes API.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Binary Structure\n\n```\ncmd/\n├── agentd/                      # Kubernetes controller (existing)\n│   └── main.go\n├── agentcube/                   # Main CLI - resource management\n│   └── main.go\n├── agentcube-admin/             # Admin CLI - cluster administration\n│   └── main.go\n├── agentcube-shell/             # Interactive shell - sandbox access\n│   └── main.go","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/cmd/design.md","time":{"start":1775864189910,"end":1775864189959}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775864189966,"sessionID":"ses_2863f3b4dffeWWPksoHTtGvb3O","part":{"id":"prt_d79c0ff92001MHbhPrDqvE0rf3","messageID":"msg_d79c0edbc0011hbhimeCRbc48d","sessionID":"ses_2863f3b4dffeWWPksoHTtGvb3O","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_d18209cb8cb04fd1b867896d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/cmd/agentd/main.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/cmd/agentd/main.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: package main\n2: \n3: import (\n4: \t\"flag\"\n5: \t\"os\"\n6: \n7: \t\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime\"\n8: \tutilruntime \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/util/runtime\"\n9: \tclientgoscheme \"k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes/scheme\"\n10: \t_ \"k8s.io/client-go/plugin/pkg/client/auth\"\n11: \tctrl \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime\"\n12: \t\"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/log/zap\"\n13: \t\"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/manager/signals\"\n14: \tmetricsserver \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/metrics/server\"\n15: \n16: \tagentd \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/agentd\"\n17: )\n18: \n19: var (\n20: \tscheme   = runtime.NewScheme()\n21: \tsetupLog = ctrl.Log.WithName(\"setup\")\n22: )\n23: \n24: func init() {\n25: \tutilruntime.Must(clientgoscheme.AddToScheme(scheme))\n26: \tutilruntime.Must(agentd.AddToScheme(scheme))\n27: }\n28: \n29: func main() {\n30: \tvar metricsAddr string\n31: \tvar enableLeaderElection bool\n32: \tvar probeAddr string\n33: \n34: \tflag.StringVar(&metricsAddr, \"metrics-bind-address\", \":8080\", \"The address the metric endpoint binds to.\")\n35: \tflag.StringVar(&probeAddr, \"health-probe-bind-address\", \":8081\", \"The address the probe endpoint binds to.\")\n36: \tflag.BoolVar(&enableLeaderElection, \"leader-elect\", false,\n37: \t\t\"Enable leader election for controller manager. \"+\n38: \t\t\t\"Enabling this will ensure there is only one active controller manager.\")\n39: \n40: \topts := zap.Options{\n41: \t\tDevelopment: true,\n42: \t}\n43: \topts.BindFlags(flag.CommandLine)\n44: \tflag.Parse()\n45: \n46: \tctrl.SetLogger(zap.New(zap.UseFlagOptions(&opts)))\n47: \n48: \tmgr, err := ctrl.NewManager(ctrl.GetConfigOrDie(), ctrl.Options{\n49: \t\tScheme: scheme,\n50: \t\tMetrics: metricsserver.Options{\n51: \t\t\tBindAddress: metricsAddr,\n52: \t\t},\n53: \t\tHealthProbeBindAddress: probeAddr,\n54: \t\tLeaderElection:         enableLeaderElection,\n55: \t\tLeaderElectionID:       \"agentd-leader\",\n56: \t})\n57: \tif err != nil {\n58: \t\tsetupLog.Error(err, \"unable to start manager\")\n59: \t\tos.Exit(1)\n60: \t}\n61: \n62: \tif err = (&agentd.Reconciler{\n63: \t\tClient: mgr.GetClient(),\n64: \t\tScheme: mgr.GetScheme(),\n65: \t}).SetupWithManager(mgr); err != nil {\n66: \t\tsetupLog.Error(err, \"unable to create controller\", \"controller\", \"Agentd\")\n67: \t\tos.Exit(1)\n68: \t}\n69: \n70: \tsetupLog.Info(\"starting manager\")\n71: \tif err := mgr.Start(signals.SetupSignalHandler()); err != nil {\n72: \t\tsetupLog.Error(err, \"problem running manager\")\n73: \t\tos.Exit(1)\n74: \t}\n75: }\n\n(End of file - total 75 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"package main\n\nimport (\n\t\"flag\"\n\t\"os\"\n\n\t\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime\"\n\tutilruntime \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/util/runtime\"\n\tclientgoscheme \"k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes/scheme\"\n\t_ \"k8s.io/client-go/plugin/pkg/client/auth\"\n\tctrl \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime\"\n\t\"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/log/zap\"\n\t\"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/manager/signals\"\n\tmetricsserver \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/metrics/server\"\n\n\tagentd \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/agentd\"\n)\n\nvar (\n\tscheme   = runtime.NewScheme()","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/cmd/agentd/mai