{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775864206053,"sessionID":"ses_2863f3b4dffeWWPksoHTtGvb3O","part":{"id":"prt_d79c14452001n6yvKrqA7zJ2IZ","messageID":"msg_d79c13782001mI64M1PRXfpelm","sessionID":"ses_2863f3b4dffeWWPksoHTtGvb3O","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_5a93d502581747aa92f928fc","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-018/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-018/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-018 — Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-018 — Agentd 空闲清理控制器 |\n8: | Module | `pkg/agentd` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | S |\n11: | Stage | ST-3 completed |\n12: \n13: ## Atomic Tasks\n14: \n15: ### Phase 1: Configuration Structure (`config.go`)\n16: \n17: - [ ] **TASK-001**: Create `pkg/agentd/config.go`\n18:   - Define package `agentd` with required imports\n19: \n20: - [ ] **TASK-002**: Define `CleanupConfig` struct in `pkg/agentd/config.go`\n21:   - Fields: `AgentRuntimeIdleTimeout time.Duration`, `CodeInterpreterIdleTimeout time.Duration`, `CleanupInterval time.Duration`, `MaxConcurrentCleanups int`, `Enabled bool`, `DryRun bool`, `NamespaceAllowList []string`, `NamespaceDenyList []string`\n22: \n23: - [ ] **TASK-003**: Implement `DefaultCleanupConfig() *CleanupConfig` in `pkg/agentd/config.go`\n24:   - Return config with: AgentRuntime timeout 30m, CodeInterpreter timeout 15m, interval 5m, max concurrent 10, enabled true, dry run false\n25: \n26: - [ ] **TASK-004**: Implement `LoadCleanupConfigFromEnv() (*CleanupConfig, error)` in `pkg/agentd/config.go`\n27:   - Load `AGENTD_CLEANUP_ENABLED` (default: true)\n28:   - Load `AGENTD_CLEANUP_DRY_RUN` (default: false)\n29:   - Load `AGENTD_AGENT_RUNTIME_IDLE_TIMEOUT` (default: 30m)\n30:   - Load `AGENTD_CODE_INTERPRETER_IDLE_TIMEOUT` (default: 15m)\n31:   - Load `AGENTD_CLEANUP_INTERVAL` (default: 5m)\n32:   - Load `AGENTD_MAX_CONCURRENT_CLEANUPS` (default: 10)\n33:   - Load `AGENTD_CLEANUP_NAMESPACE_ALLOW_LIST` (comma-separated, default: empty)\n34:   - Load `AGENTD_CLEANUP_NAMESPACE_DENY_LIST` (default: kube-system,kube-public)\n35:   - Parse duration strings, log warnings and use defaults on parse failures\n36: \n37: - [ ] **TASK-005**: Implement `Validate(c *CleanupConfig) error` in `pkg/agentd/config.go`\n38:   - Validate timeouts are positive\n39:   - Validate CleanupInterval is positive\n40:   - Validate MaxConcurrentCleanups > 0\n41:   - Validate NamespaceDenyList includes system namespaces\n42: \n43: ### Phase 2: CleanupError Types (`errors.go`)\n44: \n45: - [ ] **TASK-010**: Define `CleanupErrorType` type and constants in `pkg/agentd/errors.go`\n46:   - Type: `CleanupErrorType` (string alias)\n47:   - Constants: `CleanupErrorNotFound`, `CleanupErrorPermission`, `CleanupErrorTimeout`, `CleanupErrorConflict`, `CleanupErrorUnknown`\n48: \n49: - [ ] **TASK-011**: Define `CleanupError` struct in `pkg/agentd/errors.go`\n50:   - Fields: `Type CleanupErrorType`, `ResourceKind string`, `Namespace string`, `Name string`, `Message string`, `Underlying error`\n51:   - Method: `Error() string` with format \"cleanup error [%s] for %s/%s/%s: %s\"\n52: \n53: - [ ] **TASK-012**: Implement `NewCleanupError(errType CleanupErrorType, kind, namespace, name, message string, underlying error) *CleanupError` in `pkg/agentd/errors.go`\n54: \n55: ### Phase 3: IdleTracker Interface and Implementation (`idle_tracker.go`)\n56: \n57: - [ ] **TASK-020**: Define `ResourceKey` struct in `pkg/agentd/idle_tracker.go`\n58:   - Fields: `Kind string`, `Namespace string`, `Name string`\n59: \n60: - [ ] **TASK-021**: Define `IdleTracker` interface in `pkg/agentd/idle_tracker.go`\n61:   - Methods: `UpdateLastActivity(kind, namespace, name string, timestamp time.Time)`, `GetLastActivity(kind, namespace, name string) (time.Time, bool)`, `IsIdle(kind, namespace, name string, timeout time.Duration) bool`, `Remove(kind, namespace, name string)`, `ListIdleResources(timeout time.Duration) []ResourceKey`\n62: \n63: - [ ] **TASK-022**: Define `idleTracker` struct in `pkg/agentd/idle_tracker.go`\n64:   - Fields: `mu sync.RWMutex`, `lastActivity map[ResourceKey]time.Time`, `logger klog.Logger`\n65: \n66: - [ ] **TASK-023**: Implement `NewIdleTracker(logger klog.Logger) IdleTracker` in `pkg/agentd/idle_tracker.go`\n67:   - Initialize lastActivity map\n68:   - Return initialized tracker\n69: \n70: - [ ] **TASK-024**: Implement `UpdateLastActivity` method in `pkg/agentd/idle_tracker.go`\n71:   - Lock mutex, update map, log at V(4)\n72: \n73: - [ ] **TASK-025**: Implement `GetLastActivity` method in `pkg/agentd/idle_tracker.go`\n74:   - RLock mutex, return timestamp and exists bool\n75: \n76: - [ ] **TASK-026**: Implement `IsIdle` method in `pkg/agentd/idle_tracker.go`\n77:   - Return true if no activity recorded\n78:   - Return true if time.Since(lastActivity) >= timeout\n79:   - Return false otherwise\n80: \n81: - [ ] **TASK-027**: Implement `Remove` method in `pkg/agentd/idle_tracker.go`\n82:   - Lock mutex, delete from map\n83: \n84: - [ ] **TASK-028**: Implement `ListIdleResources` method in `pkg/agentd/idle_tracker.go`\n85:   - RLock mutex, iterate map, collect idle resources\n86: \n87: ### Phase 4: CleanupMetrics (`cleanup_metrics.go`)\n88: \n89: - [ ] **TASK-030**: Define `CleanupMetrics` struct in `pkg/agentd/cleanup_metrics.go`\n90:   - Fields: `agentRuntimeCleanupsTotal prometheus.Counter`, `codeInterpreterCleanupsTotal prometheus.Counter`, `cleanupErrorsTotal *prometheus.CounterVec`, `cleanupDurationSeconds *prometheus.HistogramVec`, `idleResourcesDetected *prometheus.GaugeVec`\n91: \n92: - [ ] **TASK-031**: Implement `NewCleanupMetrics(reg prometheus.Registerer) *CleanupMetrics` in `pkg/agentd/cleanup_metrics.go`\n93:   - Initialize all metrics with proper labels\n94:   - Register metrics with provided registerer\n95: \n96: - [ ] **TASK-032**: Implement `RecordCleanup(kind string, duration time.Duration, err error)` method in `pkg/agentd/cleanup_metrics.go`\n97:   - Increment appropriate counter based on kind\n98:   - Record duration in histogram\n99:   - Increment error counter if err != nil\n100: \n101: - [ ] **TASK-033**: Implement `SetIdleCount(kind string, count int)` method in `pkg/agentd/cleanup_metrics.go`\n102:   - Set gauge for idle resource count\n103: \n104: - [ ] **TASK-034**: Implement `RecordError(kind string)` method in `pkg/agentd/cleanup_metrics.go`\n105:   - Increment error counter with kind label\n106: \n107: ### Phase 5: IdleCleanupController Implementation (`idle_cleanup.go`)\n108: \n109: - [ ] **TASK-040**: Define `CleanupResult` struct in `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n110:   - Fields: `AgentRuntimesCleaned int`, `CodeInterpretersCleaned int`, `Errors []CleanupError`\n111: \n112: - [ ] **TASK-041**: Define `IdleCleanupController` interface in `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n113:   - Methods: `Start(ctx context.Context) error`, `Stop()`, `CleanupNow(ctx context.Context) (CleanupResult, error)`\n114: \n115: - [ ] **TASK-042**: Define `idleCleanupController` struct in `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n116:   - Fields: `config *CleanupConfig`, `agentClient versioned.Interface`, `idleTracker IdleTracker`, `metrics *CleanupMetrics`, `logger klog.Logger`, `stopCh chan struct{}`, `wg sync.WaitGroup`\n117: \n118: - [ ] **TASK-043**: Implement `NewIdleCleanupController(config *CleanupConfig, agentClient versioned.Interface, idleTracker IdleTracker, metrics *CleanupMetrics, logger klog.Logger) IdleCleanupController` in `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n119: \n120: - [ ] **TASK-044**: Implement `Start(ctx context.Context) error` method in `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n121:   - Check if enabled, return early if disabled\n122:   - Start watch goroutine for resources\n123:   - Start periodic cleanup goroutine with ticker\n124:   - Log startup message with configuration\n125: \n126: - [ ] **TASK-045**: Implement `Stop()` method in `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n127:   - Close stopCh\n128:   - Wait for goroutines to complete via wg.Wait()\n129:   - Log shutdown completion\n130: \n131: - [ ] **TASK-046**: Implement `CleanupNow(ctx context.Context) (CleanupResult, error)` method in `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n132:   - Run immediate cleanup cycle\n133:   - Return CleanupResult with counts and errors\n134: \n135: - [ ] **TASK-047**: Implement `runCleanup(ctx context.Context)` method in `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n136:   - Create errgroup with MaxConcurrentCleanups limit\n137:   - List idle AgentRuntimes and submit cleanup tasks\n138:   - List idle CodeInterpreters and submit cleanup tasks\n139:   - Wait for all tasks and log completion status\n140: \n141: - [ ] **TASK-048**: Implement `cleanupResource(ctx context.Context, kind, namespace, name string) error` method in `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n142:   - Handle DryRun mode (log only)\n143:   - Delete AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter based on kind\n144:   - Use GracePeriodSeconds: 30, PropagationPolicy: Foreground\n145:   - Record metrics\n146:   - Remove from idle tracker on success\n147:   - Handle NotFound errors gracefully\n148: \n149: - [ ] **TASK-049**: Implement `isNamespaceAllowed(namespace string) bool` method in `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n150:   - Check deny list first (returns false if matched)\n151:   - Check allow list (returns true if empty or matched)\n152: \n153: ### Phase 6: Resource Watching (`idle_cleanup.go`)\n154: \n155: - [ ] **TASK-050**: Implement `watchResources(ctx context.Context)` method in `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n156:   - Start watchAgentRuntimes goroutine\n157:   - Start watchCodeInterpreters goroutine\n158:   - Wait for context cancellation\n159: \n160: - [ ] **TASK-051**: Implement `watchAgentRuntimes(ctx context.Context)` method in `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n161:   - 