ent idle cleanup controller\n331:   - Include configuration options and environment variables\n332:   - Include metrics documentation\n333:   - Include operational guide\n334: \n335: - [ ] **DOC-004**: Add security and operations documentation\n336:   - Namespace isolation considerations\n337:   - RBAC requirements\n338:   - Monitoring and alerting recommendations\n339: \n340: ## Acceptance Criteria\n341: \n342: - [ ] `IdleCleanupController` interface implements all required methods\n343: - [ ] `IdleTracker` correctly tracks last activity timestamps\n344: - [ ] Idle detection works with configurable timeouts per resource type\n345: - [ ] Namespace allow/deny lists are respected\n346: - [ ] Dry-run mode logs without deleting\n347: - [ ] Concurrent cleanup limits are enforced\n348: - [ ] Metrics are exposed for monitoring\n349: - [ ] Watch reconnection handles connection failures\n350: - [ ] All unit tests pass\n351: - [ ] Integration tests pass with fake clients\n352: - [ ] Code coverage >= 80%\n353: - [ ] Documentation includes configuration examples\n354: - [ ] Graceful shutdown on controller stop\n355: - [ ] All files have corresponding test files\n356: \n357: ## Dependencies\n358: \n359: | Dependency | Source | Usage |\n360: |------------|--------|-------|\n361: | `k8s.io/client-go` | External | Kubernetes client interfaces |\n362: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Generated | Typed client for runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh |\n363: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` | Generated | AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter types |\n364: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/watch` | External | Watch event streaming |\n365: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1` | External | Metadata, deletion options |\n366: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | External | Structured logging |\n367: | `prometheus/client_golang/prometheus` | External | Metrics exposition |\n368: | `golang.org/x/sync/errgroup` | External | Concurrent cleanup with limits |\n369: \n370: ## Implemen