PrivateKey, *rsa.PublicKey, error)` in `pkg/picod/crypto.go`\n36:   - Generate RSA key pair using rsa.GenerateKey\n37:   - Return private and public keys\n38:   - Use crypto/rand for secure random generation\n39: \n40: ### Phase 2: JWT Claims & Validation (`jwt.go`)\n41: \n42: - [ ] **TASK-010**: Define `Claims` struct in `pkg/picod/jwt.go`\n43:   - Fields: `Sub` (string), `Iss` (string), `Aud` (string), `Exp` (int64), `Iat` (int64), `SandboxID` (string), `Namespace` (string)\n44:   - JSON tags for all fields\n45: \n46: - [ ] **TASK-011**: Implement `Validate(c *Claims, now time.Time, clockSkew time.Duration) error` in `pkg/picod/jwt.go`\n47:   - Check expiration (exp + clockSkew < now → expired)\n48:   - Check not before (iat - clockSkew > now → not yet valid)\n49:   - Validate required claims (sub, iss, aud, exp, iat present)\n50:   - Return appropriate error for each validation failure\n51: \n52: - [ ] **TASK-012**: Implement `ParseAndValidate(tokenString string, publicKey *rsa.PublicKey, clockSkew time.Duration) (*Claims, error)` in `pkg/picod/jwt.go`\n53:   - Split token into header.payload.signature\n54:   - Verify signature using VerifySignature\n55:   - Parse payload JSON into Claims\n56:   - Validate claims using Validate\n57:   - Return parsed claims or error\n58: \n59: - [ ] **TASK-013**: Implement `VerifySignature(tokenString string, publicKey *rsa.PublicKey) error` in `pkg/picod/jwt.go`\n60:   - Decode header and payload (base64url)\n61:   - Decode signature (base64url)\n62:   - Construct signing input: `header.payload`\n63:   - Verify RSA-PKCS1v15 signature (SHA256)\n64:   - Return error if signature invalid\n65: \n66: ### Phase 3: Authentication Errors (`errors.go`)\n67: \n68: - [ ] **TASK-020**: Define `AuthErrorType` type and constants in `pkg/picod/errors.go`\n69:   - Type: `AuthErrorType` (string alias)\n70:   - Constants: `AuthErrorMissingToken`, `AuthErrorInvalidToken`, `AuthErrorExpiredToken`, `AuthErrorInvalidSig`, `AuthErrorInvalidClaims`, `AuthErrorInternal`\n71: \n72: - [ ] **TASK-021**: Define `AuthError` struct in `pkg/picod/errors.go`\n73:   - Fields: `Type` (AuthErrorType), `Message` (string), `Underlying` (error)\n74:   - Methods: `Error() string`, `Unwrap() error`\n75: \n76: - [ ] **TASK-022**: Implement `HTTPStatus(e *AuthError) int` in `pkg/picod/errors.go`\n77:   - Map error types to HTTP status codes:\n78:     - MissingToken, InvalidToken, InvalidSig, InvalidClaims → 401\n79:     - ExpiredToken → 401\n80:     - Internal → 500\n81: \n82: - [ ] **TASK-023**: Implement `NewAuthError(authType AuthErrorType, message string, underlying error) *AuthError` in `pkg/picod/errors.go`\n83:   - Constructor for AuthError\n84:   - Format message with context\n85: \n86: ### Phase 4: HTTP Middleware (`middleware.go`)\n87: \n88: - [ ] **TASK-030**: Define `JWTMiddleware` struct in `pkg/picod/middleware.go`\n89:   - Fields: `publicKey` (*rsa.PublicKey), `skipPaths` (map[string]bool), `clockSkew` (time.Duration), `logger` (klog.Logger)\n90: \n91: - [ ] **TASK-031**: Implement `NewJWTMiddleware(publicKey *rsa.PublicKey, clockSkew time.Duration, skipPaths ...string) *JWTMiddleware` in `pkg/picod/middleware.go`\n92:   - Initialize skipPaths map\n93:   - Set default clockSkew (30 seconds if 0)\n94:   - Create structured logger\n95: \n96: - [ ] **TASK-032**: Implement `Middleware(m *JWTMiddleware, next http.Handler) http.Handler` in `pkg/picod/middleware.go`\n97:   - Wrap handler with authentication logic\n98:   - Extract path from request\n99:   - Check if path should skip auth\n100:   - Extract token from Authorization header\n101:   - Validate token\n102:   - Call next handler on success, return error on failure\n103: \n104: - [ ] **TASK-033**: Implement `extractToken(m *JWTMiddleware, r *http.Request) (string, error)` in `pkg/picod/middleware.go`\n105:   - Get Authorization header\n106:   - Validate \"Bearer \" prefix\n107:   - Extract token string\n108:   - Return error if missing or malformed\n109: \n110: - [ ] **TASK-034**: Implement `shouldSkip(m *JWTMiddleware, path string) bool` in `pkg/picod/middleware.go`\n111:   - Check if path exists in skipPaths map\n112:   - Support exact path matching\n113: \n114: ### Phase 5: HTTP Response Helpers (`middleware.go`)\n115: \n116: - [ ] **TASK-040**: Implement `WriteJSON(w http.ResponseWriter, status int, data interface{})` in `pkg/picod/middleware.go`\n117:   - Set Content-Type header\n118:   - Set status code\n119:   - Encode data as JSON\n120:   - Handle encoding errors\n121: \n122: - [ ] **TASK-041**: Implement `WriteAuthError(w http.ResponseWriter, err *AuthError)` in `pkg/picod/middleware.go`\n123:   - Get HTTP status from error\n124:   - Write JSON error response\n125:   - Include error type and message\n126: \n127: - [ ] **TASK-042**: Define `HealthResponse` struct in `pkg/picod/middleware.go`\n128:   - Fields: `Status` (string), `Timestamp` (time.Time), `SandboxID` (string)\n129:   - JSON tags for all fields\n130: \n131: ### Phase 6: Configuration (`config.go`)\n132: \n133: - [ ] **TASK-050**: Add auth fields to `Config` struct in `pkg/picod/config.go`\n134:   - Fields: `AuthMode` (string), `PublicKeyPEM` (string), `SkipPaths` ([]string), `ClockSkew` (time.Duration)\n135: \n136: - [ ] **TASK-051**: Update `LoadConfig()` in `pkg/picod/config.go`\n137:   - Load `PICOD_AUTH_MODE` (default: \"none\")\n138:   - Load `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` (required if AuthMode=picod)\n139:   - Load `PICOD_AUTH_SKIP_PATHS` (default: \"/health\", comma-separated)\n140:   - Load `PICOD_AUTH_CLOCK_SKEW` (default: 30s)\n141: \n142: - [ ] **TASK-052**: Add command-line flag parsing helpers in `pkg/picod/config.go`\n143:   - `ParseAuthFlags()` function\n144:   - Flags: `-auth`, `-public-key`, `-skip-paths`, `-clock-skew`\n145:   - Merge flags with environment variables (flags take precedence)\n146: \n147: - [ ] **TASK-053**: Implement `Validate(c *Config) error` for auth config in `pkg/picod/config.go`\n148:   - If AuthMode=\"picod\", require PublicKeyPEM\n149:   - Validate clockSkew is non-negative\n150:   - Parse and validate skip paths\n151: \n152: ### Phase 7: PicoD Integration (`picod.go`)\n153: \n154: - [ ] **TASK-060**: Add `authMode` and `publicKey` fields to `PicoD` struct in `pkg/picod/picod.go`\n155:   - Fields: `authMode` (string), `publicKey` (*rsa.PublicKey)\n156: \n157: - [ ] **TASK-061**: Add `WithAuthMode(mode string) Option` in `pkg/picod/picod.go`\n158:   - Functional option to set auth mode\n159: \n160: - [ ] **TASK-062**: Add `WithPublicKey(pem string) Option` in `pkg/picod/picod.go`\n161:   - Functional option to set public key\n162:   - Load key from PEM\n163: \n164: - [ ] **TASK-063**: Implement `SetupHTTPServer(picod *PicoD, config *Config) (*http.Server, error)` in `pkg/picod/picod.go`\n165:   - Create ServeMux\n166:   - Register handlers\n167:   - Apply JWT middleware if AuthMode=picod\n168:   - Configure ReadHeaderTimeout (10s)\n169: \n170: ### Phase 8: Unit Tests\n171: \n172: #### Crypto Tests\n173: \n174: - [ ] **TEST-001**: Create `TestLoadPublicKey_Success` in `pkg/picod/crypto_test.go`\n175:   - Load valid PKIX PEM key\n176:   - Verify key returned without error\n177: \n178: - [ ] **TEST-002**: Create `TestLoadPublicKeyFromBase64` in `pkg/picod/crypto_test.go`\n179:   - Load base64-encoded PEM key\n180:   - Verify decoded key matches direct load\n181: \n182: - [ ] **TEST-003**: Create `TestLoadPublicKey_InvalidPEM` in `pkg/picod/crypto_test.go`\n183:   - Load invalid PEM data\n184:   - Verify error returned\n185: \n186: - [ ] **TEST-004**: Create `TestGenerateKeyPair` in `pkg/picod/crypto_test.go`\n187:   - Generate key pair (2048 bits)\n188:   - Verify private and public keys not nil\n189: \n190: #### JWT Tests\n191: \n192: - [ ] **TEST-010**: Create `TestClaims_Validate_Success` in `pkg/picod/jwt_test.go`\n193:   - Valid claims with future exp\n194:   - Verify no error\n195: \n196: - [ ] **TEST-011**: Create `TestClaims_Validate_Expired` in `pkg/picod/jwt_test.go`\n197:   -