{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775864338662,"sessionID":"ses_2863f3b4dffeWWPksoHTtGvb3O","part":{"id":"prt_d79c178e4001jjNIgfrK4YY4sD","messageID":"msg_d79c15326001hhY5dzBnbdryz5","sessionID":"ses_2863f3b4dffeWWPksoHTtGvb3O","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_a5a363f5d9084afe92d41581","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-019/tasks.md","content":"# AR-019 — CLI Binary Entry Points Tasks\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-019 — CLI 二进制入口 (4 binaries) |\n| Module | `cmd` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-3 completed |\n\n## Atomic Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: Version Package (`pkg/version/version.go`)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-001**: Create `pkg/version/version.go`\n  - Define package `version` with required imports\n\n- [ ] **TASK-002**: Define package-level variables in `pkg/version/version.go`\n  - `Version string` (default: \"0.0.0\")\n  - `GitCommit string` (default: \"unknown\")\n  - `BuildDate string` (default: \"unknown\")\n  - `GoVersion string` (default: \"unknown\")\n\n- [ ] **TASK-003**: Define `Info` struct in `pkg/version/version.go`\n  - Fields: `Version`, `GitCommit`, `BuildDate`, `GoVersion` (all string, with json tags)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-004**: Implement `Get() Info` in `pkg/version/version.go`\n  - Return Info struct with all version variables\n\n- [ ] **TASK-005**: Implement `String() string` in `pkg/version/version.go`\n  - Return formatted version string (e.g., \"version/gitCommit/buildDate/goVersion\")\n\n### Phase 2: CLI Common Configuration (`pkg/cli/common/config.go`)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-010**: Create `pkg/cli/common/config.go`\n  - Define package `common` with required imports (spf13/viper, k8s.io/client-go/util/homedir, filepath, os)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-011**: Define `CLIConfig` struct in `pkg/cli/common/config.go`\n  - Fields: `Kubeconfig string`, `Namespace string`, `Timeout int`, `Output string`, `LogLevel string` (all with mapstructure tags)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-012**: Implement `LoadConfig() (*CLIConfig, error)` in `pkg/cli/common/config.go`\n  - Configure viper with config name \"config\", type \"yaml\"\n  - Add config paths: ~/.agentcube, current directory\n  - Enable automatic environment variables\n  - Set defaults (kubeconfig=\"\", namespace=\"default\", timeout=30, output=\"table\", log-level=\"info\")\n  - Handle ConfigFileNotFoundError gracefully\n  - Override Kubeconfig with KUBECONFIG env var if set\n  - Return config or error\n\n- [ ] **TASK-013**: Implement `GetClientset(config *CLIConfig) (*versioned.Clientset, error)` in `pkg/cli/common/config.go`\n  - Build kubeconfig from flags/env\n  - Create and return typed clientset\n  - Return error on failure\n\n### Phase 3: CLI Output Helpers (`pkg/cli/common/output.go`)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-020**: Create `pkg/cli/common/output.go`\n  - Define package `common` with required imports (encoding/json, fmt, os, gopkg.in/yaml.v3)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-021**: Implement `PrintObject(obj runtime.Object, format string) error` in `pkg/cli/common/output.go`\n  - Switch on format: json, yaml, table\n  - JSON: encode with indentation\n  - YAML: marshal to JSON first, then convert to YAML\n  - Table: return error (not supported for generic objects)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-022**: Implement `PrintTable(headers []string, rows [][]string)` in `pkg/cli/common/output.go`\n  - Calculate column widths\n  - Print formatted table with proper alignment\n\n- [ ] **TASK-023**: Implement `jsonToYAML(data []byte) ([]byte, error)` in `pkg/cli/common/output.go`\n  - Convert JSON to YAML using yaml.v3\n\n### Phase 4: picod Binary (`cmd/picod/main.go`)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-030**: Create `cmd/picod/main.go`\n  - Define package `main` with required imports (flag, net/http, os, strings)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-031**: Define CLI flags in `cmd/picod/main.go`\n  - `-port` (int, default: 8080)\n  - `-workspace` (string, default: \".\")\n  - `-auth` (string, default: \"none\")\n  - `-public-key` (string, default: \"\")\n  - `-skip-paths` (string, default: \"/health\")\n\n- [ ] **TASK-032**: Implement `main()` in `cmd/picod/main.go`\n  - Parse flags\n  - Load config from flags and env\n  - Get SANDBOX_ID from env\n  - Create PicoD instance with functional options\n  - Setup HTTP server with optional JWT middleware\n  - Start server on specified port\n  - Handle server errors with klog\n\n### Phase 5: agentcube CLI Root (`cmd/agentcube/main.go`)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-040**: Create `cmd/agentcube/main.go`\n  - Define package `main` with required imports (os, spf13/cobra)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-041**: Implement `NewRootCommand() *cobra.Command` in `cmd/agentcube/main.go`\n  - Use: \"agentcube\"\n  - Short/Long description\n  - Add subcommands: agentruntime, codeinterpreter, version, completion\n\n- [ ] **TASK-042**: Implement `main()` in `cmd/agentcube/main.go`\n  - Execute root command\n  - Exit with code 1 on error\n\n- [ ] **TASK-043**: Create `cmd/agentcube/version.go`\n  - Implement versionCmd (cobra.Command)\n  - Print version info from pkg/version.Get()\n\n- [ ] **TASK-044**: Create `cmd/agentcube/completion.go`\n  - Implement completionCmd (cobra.Command)\n  - Support bash, zsh, fish, powershell\n  - Generate completion scripts\n\n### Phase 6: agentruntime Commands (`pkg/cli/agentruntime/`)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-050**: Create `pkg/cli/agentruntime/agentruntime.go`\n  - Define `agentRuntimeOptions` struct (kubeconfig, namespace, timeout, output)\n  - Implement `NewAgentRuntimeCommand() *cobra.Command`\n  - Add persistent flags: kubeconfig, namespace, output\n  - Add subcommands: create, get, list, update, delete, describe, logs\n\n- [ ] **TASK-051**: Create `pkg/cli/agentruntime/list.go`\n  - Implement `NewAgentRuntimeListCommand(o *agentRuntimeOptions) *cobra.Command`\n  - Use: \"list [NAME]\", Aliases: [\"ls\"]\n  - List AgentRuntimes in namespace\n  - Support label selector via -l flag\n  - Call `printAgentRuntimeList(list)`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-052**: Implement `printAgentRuntimeList(list *AgentRuntimeList, format string)` in `pkg/cli/agentruntime/list.go`\n  - JSON: encode with indentation\n  - YAML: convert to YAML\n  - Table: print NAME, NAMESPACE, STATUS, CREATED columns\n\n- [ ] **TASK-053**: Create `pkg/cli/agentruntime/get.go`\n  - Implement `NewAgentRuntimeGetCommand(o *agentRuntimeOptions) *cobra.Command`\n  - Use: \"get NAME\"\n  - Get single AgentRuntime by name\n  - Support -o flag for output format\n\n- [ ] **TASK-054**: Create `pkg/cli/agentruntime/describe.go`\n  - Implement `NewAgentRuntimeDescribeCommand(o *agentRuntimeOptions) *cobra.Command`\n  - Use: \"describe NAME\"\n  - Show detailed info: spec, status, events, conditions\n\n- [ ] **TASK-055**: Create `pkg/cli/agentruntime/create.go`\n  - Implement `NewAgentRuntimeCreateCommand(o *agentRuntimeOptions) *cobra.Command`\n  - Use: \"create NAME\"\n  - Flags: --image, --namespace, --cpu, --memory, --labels\n  - Construct AgentRuntime object\n  - Call K8s API to create\n\n- [ ] **TASK-056**: Create `pkg/cli/agentruntime/update.go`\n  - Implement `NewAgentRuntimeUpdateCommand(o *agentRuntimeOptions) *cobra.Command`\n  - Use: \"update NAME\"\n  - Flags: --image, --cpu, --memory (partial updates)\n  - Fetch existing, apply changes, update\n\n- [ ] **TASK-057**: Create `pkg/cli/agentruntime/delete.go`\n  - Implement `NewAgentRuntimeDeleteCommand(o *agentRuntimeOptions) *cobra.Command`\n  - Use: \"delete NAME\"\n  - Flags: --force, --grace-period\n  - Delete with confirmation prompt (unless --force)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-058**: Create `pkg/cli/agentruntime/logs.go`\n  - Implement `NewAgentRuntimeLogsCommand(o *agentRuntimeOptions) *cobra.Command`\n  - Use: \"logs NAME\"\n  - Flags: --follow, --tail, --since, --container\n  - Stream pod logs using k8s API\n\n### Phase 7: codeinterpreter Commands (`pkg/cli/codeinterpreter/`)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-060**: Create `pkg/cli/codeinterpreter/codeinterpreter.go`\n  - Define `codeInterpreterOptions` struct\n  - Implemen